name: gpcAttributeValueName
definition: The GS1 provided text equivalent of the Global Product Classification Attribute Value Code.

name: flammableAerosolContainmentCode
definition: Determines whether the propellant in the trade item is an aerosol and whether the aerosol is considered flammable.

name: tradeItemKeyWords
definition: Words or phrases that enables web search engines to find trade items on the internet for example Shampoo, Lather, Baby.

name: childNutritionExpirationDateTime
definition: The date upon which the child nutrition statement or label expires.

name: fieldOfView
definition: Real field of view (field of vision) is the angle of the visible field, seen without moving the item, measured from the central point of the objective lens. In games the extent of the observable world that is seen at any given moment. This is used by such items as: microscope, rifle scope, cameras, binoculars are just some type of items. Measure in linear length or angular degrees for example 300 metres (MTR), 45 degrees(DD).

name: audioVisualMediaProductCollectionSeriesNumber
definition: Denotes which part of the series the media is part of for example Halloween II, Law & Order 7, South Park Season 12, Terminator 3, Star Wars II.

name: alternateText
definition: A detailed information pertaining to the image and the context for someone who is partially or fully visually impaired or blind

name: fileOptimalViewerName
definition: The software to which this file was targeted.

name: specialRequirementsDescription
definition: Any special requirements for storage or transportation in relation to any hazardous materials for example those regulated by ADR (European Agreement concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road).

name: audioVisualMediaProductCollectionName
definition: The name of a series of music publications grouped under a common theme. The name of the collection is printed on the package of the trade item.

name: lastChangeDate
definition: The date the party was last changed in the Global Registry

name: isPartyActive
definition: A Boolean field used to express whether the party is active or inactive used for tracking billing

name: freeQuantityOfProduct
definition: To indicate the quantity which is free.  It is needed to update the price per unit of measure as displayed on the shelves.  The unit of measure must be the same as the unit of measure of the Net Content.  If the free quantity is expressed on the package it must be converted to a quantity expressed in the same unit of meas-ure as the net content in the message.

name: tradeItemTemperatureConditionTypeCode
definition: The condition of the product sold to the end consumer for example thawed or frozen.

name: globalModelRegulatoryAct
definition: The regulatory act that the Global Model Number is aligned to.

name: rugTypeCode
definition: A code indicating the usage or intended room for a particular type of rug.

name: sportCode
definition: A code indicating the sport associated with the product.

name: titlePrefixType
definition: Text at the beginning of a title element which is to be ignored for alphabetical sorting. Optional and non-repeating; can only be used if the <TitleWithoutPrefix> element is also present. These two elements may be used in combination in applications where it is necessary to distinguish an initial word or character string which is to be ignored for filing purposes, eg in library systems and in some bookshop databases.

name: materialAgencyCode
definition: This element indicates the agency that is maintaining the Trade Item Material codes. This may include a specific code list.

name: hazardousMaterialsHandlingProcedures
definition: Hazardous materials handling procedures are a description of how the product should be handled in relation to potential hazardous materials for example "do not handle around food, avoid contact with eyes, keep container closed.

name: minimumFishMeatPoultryContent
definition: The minimum amount of fish, meat or poultry contained in a food and beverage trade item expressed as a measurement.

name: cancelledDateTime
definition: Date on which the cancellation of the launch of a trade item what was never and will never be manufactured is made.

name: creditableAmount
definition: The creditable amount of the provided creditable ingredient as listed in the Creditable Ingredient Description and calculated as specified in the requirements, rules and regulations set forth by the applicable Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body.

name: processCapabilityEffectiveEndDateTime
definition: The date at which the registration of a process capability is no longer effective.

name: consumerFirstDeliveryDate
definition: The first date/time that the buyer is allowed to deliver or ship the trade item to consumers. Usually related to a specific geography.

name: animalNutrientQuantityContainedBasis
definition: The basis amount that the animal nutrient quantity contained is measured against for example, 12 Kilograms in the case of 3 grams per 12 kilogram.

name: lethalConcentration50
definition: Median Lethal Concentration is a statistically derived concentration of a substance that can be expected to cause death in 50% of test animals. It is usually expressed as the weight of substance per weight or volume of water, air or feed, e.g., mg/l, mg/kg or ppm.

name: avpList
definition: Attribute value pair information.

name: specificGravityMeasurementPrecision
definition: The measurement precision used for the specific gravity for example EXACT.

name: organicClaimAgencyCode
definition: A Governing body that creates and maintains standards related to organic products.

name: microbiologicalOrganismWarningValue
definition:
A microbiological limit which, in a 3–class plan, separates marginally acceptable quality from defective quality.
Exceeding the limits of the allowed content of micro organisms defined as warning values indicating there is a poor quality of the hygiene standard in the food production. This would probably lead to health hazards.

name: foodBeverageCompositionCode
definition: A value assigned by the agency for the lookup of food composition information that applies to regulatory nutrition information e.g. R851011.

name: productActivityRegionDescription
definition: The region in which a processing or other activity has been performed for example bottling, farming, last processing.

name: additionalTradeItemClassificationCodeSequenceNumber
definition: A sequence number indicating the order number of the group of properties belonging together.

name: meatPoultryCut
definition: The description of a piece of meat that has been cut from an animal carcass. The determination of this is made by the supplier and is subject to target market regulations or trade organization guidelines.

name: restrictionDescription
definition: A description on any restrictions on usage for example locations where a pesticide cannot be sold.

name: hazardousSubstancesMinimizationCode
definition: Assessment and minimization of substances, or mixtures, hazardous to the environment in packaging constituents, components, or systems that are at risk of entering the environment.

name: dispenserTypeCode
definition: The mechanism or method by which the product is dispensed from its container.

name: workingPressureRatingMinimum
definition: The minimum approved working pressure rating for the product for a specific medium state (water, gas, etc).

name: distributionMethodCode
definition: The mode by which the Information Provider and the Party Receiving Private Data have agreed at what point(s) in the supply chain the Information Provider makes the goods available to the Party Receiving Private Data.

name: dateOfCatchProcessTypeCode
definition: The process of how the fish is dated, for example REAL_TIME as fish are caught they are dated and time stamped like tuna, ONE_TIME_CATCH on a date for fish farming, or PERIODIC_CATCH meaning the catch date reflective of seasonal catch like lobster trapping.

name: organicClaimAgencyTypeCode
definition: A code depicting whether an organic agency manages organic standards or issues certifications.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: contextIdentification
definition: The unique identifier established for the business context established by GS1.

name: lastChangedDateTime
definition: Date assigned by system indicating last time the information was changed. This date is generic and will be stored where assigned and will accompany every message.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: codeListVersion
definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

name: nestingIncrement
definition: Indicates the incremental height of Trade Items nested together. In the case of two garbage cans nested together, this would be the height between the lip of the lower can and the lip on the upper can.

name: effectiveEndDateTime
definition: A date\time used to indicate when the component depicted in the segment is no longer available for use.

name: gpcAttributeTypeName
definition: The GS1 provided text equivalent of the Global Product Classification Attribute Code.

name: foodBeverageCompositionDescription
definition: A text description of either the associated value or the actual database entry lookup for example chicken soup clear instant.

name: maximumBatteryLife
definition: The maximum capacity of the battery, before it decreases with time and usage. It should be associated to the Battery Type in case a trade item has 2 different types of batteries. The different batteries could have different battery life.

name: isActiveDevice
definition: Indication if the Basic UDI-DI (Global Model Number) is an Active device. 'Active' means any device, the operation of which depends on a source of energy other than that generated by the human body for that purpose, or by gravity, and which acts by changing the density of or converting that energy.  Devices intended to transmit energy, substances or other elements between an active device and the patient, without any significant change, shall not be deemed to be active devices. Software shall also be deemed to be an active device.

name: workingPressureRatingMaximum
definition: The maximum approved working pressure rating for the product for a specific medium state (water, gas, etc).

name: doesTradeItemContainNoncreditableGrains
definition: An indication that the item contains non-creditable grains.  The existence of non-creditable grains in excess of specified limits may alter the item’s credit toward child nutrition requirements as specified by the applicable Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body.

name: isProhibitedForTransportation
definition: Indicates whether an item is prohibited for transportation via a specified mode.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: lethalConcentration50MeasurementPrecision
definition: The measurement precision used to determine the lethal concentration 50 for example EXACT.

name: quantityOfChildren
definition: Value indicates the number of unique next lower level trade items contained in a complex trade item. A complex trade item can contain at least 2 different GTINs.

name: globalWarmingPotentialEquivalentBasisYearsCode
definition:
The time perspective over which global warming potential is considered (20, 100, 500 years).
Use the characterization factors of the 4<sup>th</sup> assessment report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). 
A 100 year time perspective is recommended. The time perspective chosen should always be communicated together with the metric.

name: minimumAmountOfAnimalProtein
definition: Indicate the minimum amount of animal meat (or poultry) protein contained in the product. The determination of this is made by the supplier and may be subject to target market regulations or trade organization guidelines.

name: regulatedChemicalSunsetDateTime
definition: As the date from which the placing on the market and the use of a substance is prohibited or restricted.

name: creditableGrainAmountPerPortion
definition: The gram per portion value of the creditable grains contained in the trade item  as specified on the Product Formulation Statement and defined by the requirements, rules and regulations set forth by the applicable product formulation statement regulatory body.

name: sourceDataPool
definition: A data pool that supports the functionality required by a Data Source such as Data Loading, Publication, Notification, Registration, etc.

name: nonhazardousWasteDescription
definition: A classification of non-hazardous waste managed at the federal or state level for example a code for disposal of latex paint.

name: growingMethodCode
definition: The code indicating how the product has been grown, cultivated, reared and/or raised.

name: registrationDate
definition: The date the party was registered in the Global Registry

name: logisticsUnitCubeDimension
definition: The dimensions of an imaginary cube which can be drawn around both the unit load (content) and the platform upon which the goods are carried if there is one, as defined in the formula of H X W X D (the linear dimensions multiplied to get a cubic result).

name: rawMaterialIrradiatedCode
definition: Indicates if radiation has been applied to a trade item’s raw material.

name: bitternessOfBeerMeasurement
definition: Indicates the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the bitterness of beer, expressed in IBU and/or EBU .

name: criteriaJoinType
definition: A code that allows adjacent (as defined by Search Criteria Sequence) Search Criteria logic to be linked by adding (AND) or providing more options (OR).

name: yearOfProduction
definition: The year during which the film was produced.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: nutrientValueDerivationCode
definition: The derivation of the values, percent of intake and quantity contained, provided in the nutrient class.

name: priceValueQualifier
definition: A code assigned to identify the basis on which a specific price value is acted upon. For example, if the Price Value was 2%, the Price Value Qualifier would be ‘percent’.

name: toxicityReferenceSubstanceCode
definition: The reference substance or unit which is used to represent cancerous toxicity effects.

name: nameTypeCode
definition: Indicates the type of the name

name: countrySubdivisionCode
definition: The country subdivision in which a processing or other activity has been performed for example processing, bottling, manufacturing.

name: dutyFeeTaxRate
definition: The current tax or duty rate percentage applicable to the trade item.

name: hazardStatementsDescription
definition: A description of standard phrases assigned to a hazard class and category that describe the nature of the hazard..

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: creditableIngredientDescription
definition: A description of the trade item's creditable ingredient applicable to the creditable ingredient type and as noted on the Product Formulation Statement.  In the US, this description should be from the Food Buying Guide or an Alternate Protein Product letter (APP) or a Child Nutrition Source Label.

name: quantityOfNextLowerLevelTradeItem
definition: The number of one child trade item (as identified by the association of ChildTradeItem class to TradeItemIdentification class) contained by the parent trade item. The child trade item must be in the hierarchy level immediately below the parent trade item.

name: amountPerUnit
definition: Allowance/charge per unit expressed as an amount.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: upperExplosiveLimit
definition: The high end value expressed as a percent by volume that the product will still explode.

name: dangerousGoodsTechnicalName
definition: Provides the dangerous goods technical information.

name: dexterityUsageCode
definition: A code describing the type of handedness the trade item is designed to be used for example LEFT_HANDED, RIGHT_HANDED, etc.

name: targetConsumerAge
definition: Identifies the target consumer age range for which a trade item has been designed.

name: fatPercentageInDryMatterMeasurementPrecisionCode
definition: A code qualifying the percentage of fat in dry matter, for example LESS_THAN

name: multiComponentDeviceTypeCode
definition: The device is either a system which is a device in itself, a procedure pack which is a device in itself or kit (only applicable in case of IVDR Devices). This is a applicable for standard devices (not systems or procedure packs). For example in the EU (in accordance with the Art. 22(4) MDR).

name: functionalBasisUnitCode
definition: Code of the functional basis unit.

name: numberOfFacilitiesInStressedWaterArea
definition: The number of facilities involved with the production of packaging materials (including recycled materials), packaging constituents, packaging components or units of packaging and/or filling and sealing of units of packaging that operate in areas identified as stressed or scarce fresh water resource area.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: editionNumber
definition: The number of a numbered edition. Optional and non-repeating. Normally sent only for the second and subsequent editions of a work, but by agreement between parties to an ONIX exchange a first edition may be explicitly numbered.

name: pillowShapeCode
definition: A code indicating the shape of a pillow.

name: recommendedUsageLocation
definition: The primary location recommended for the item's use for example indoor, outdoor, indoor/outdoor, vehicle, kitchen, etc.

name: isTradeItemNonphysical
definition: An indicator that the trade item is not a physical item and as such has no dimensional manifestation.  For example a computer download of software, movies or music, a service agreement, or prepaid cellular time.

name: firstAidProceduresDescription
definition: A description of any first aid procedures necessary in case of exposure.  Note: This is used in compliance with ADR (European Agreement concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road).

name: attributeCode
definition: The value associated with the codeListName for example MLT for MEASUREMENT_CODE.

name: deviceSubStatusStartDateTime
definition: The date time when the sub-status of the medical device begins for the EU Market.

name: fileLifestyleDescription
definition: The lifestyles to which this digital asset can be used.  For example psychographic, demographic, age, etc.

name: clinicalSizeTypeCode
definition: The qualifier to denote the dimensional size which is clinically relevant for the use of the trade item by the clinical user.  For example "NEEDLE_GAUGE" for a 16 gauge needle, or "VOLUME" for a 200 cc syringe.

name: minimumOptimumConsumptionTemperature
definition: The lower limit drinking temperature of the optimum range of the drinking temperature.  The optimum range of the drinking temperature is a recommendation and is based on the experience of the individual producer.

name: feedAdditiveStatement
definition: List of the substances added to feed during processing, as for preservation, coloring, or stabilization as governed by local rules and regulations.

name: publishingStatusCode
definition: Identifies the status of a published product

name: postConsumerRecycledContentPercentage
definition: Indicates the percentage of post-consumer material used in the trade item. The post-consumer material is collected from recycle bins and used as pulp to make new items. The percentage of post-consumer material is needed to drive whether the recycled logo goes on the item. Some post-consumer material is collected from the recycle bins and used as pulp to make new items.

name: numberOfIllustrations
definition: The number of illustrations or other content items of the type specified. Optional and non-repeating.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: juiceContentPercent
definition: The fruit juice content of the trade item expressed as a percentage.

name: codeListVersion
definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

name: communicationChannelName
definition: The name of a specific communication channel for example Facebook, Twitter, etc.

name: nonfoodIngredientCodeReference
definition: A code from a specific code list for a nonFood ingredient.

name: materialPercentage
definition: Net weight percentage of a product material of the first main material.  The percent-ages must add up to 100.

name: targetSkinTypeCode
definition: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify different types of skin the product is intended for.

name: certificationIdentification
definition: A reference issued to confirm that something has passed certification.

name: sleeveType
definition: A free text description of the garment sleeve type.

name: alcoholProof
definition: Alcohol proof is a measure of how much ethanol (alcohol) is contained in an alcoholic beverage.

name: maximumAvailableStorageCapacity
definition: The maximum data storage capacity available within the trade item for electronic file storage hardware.

name: rEACHChemicalRegistrationNumber
definition: A unique registration number for a chemical for a company. This is issued by the European Chemical Agency (ECHA) and is unique per chemical.

name: mountLocationDescription
definition: A description of how the item is mounted for use especially with shelves for example on the wall, ceiling or floor.

name: shippingContainerQuantityDescription
definition: The quantity of the contents of the shipping container as described on the outside of the shipping container, for example 100 .5 oz envelopes.

name: fileVersion
definition: A description of the terms used by the manufacturer to denote the version of the digital asset.

name: maximumTemperature
definition: Specifies the upper limit of the temperature range.

name: ingredientOfConcernCode
definition: Indicates a claim to an ingredient, considered to be a concern for regulatory or other reasons, and which is “contained” within the trade item but may not need to specify the amount whether approximate, or an accurate measurement be given.

name: controlOfHazardousSubstancesRegulationsAgency
definition: The government or agency that owns regulation controlling hazard substances that may apply to the product.

name: lethalDose50
definition:
Lethal Dose 50 is a statistically derived single dose that can be expected to cause death in 50% 
of the test animals when administered by the route indicated (oral, dermal, inhalation). It is expressed as a weight of substance per unit weight of animal, e.g., mg/kg.

name: childNutritionQualifierCode
definition: A qualifier to specify the type of equivalent measurement that is applicable to the item as specified in the child nutrition statement or label. Example: FRUIT_VEGETABLE_OR_FRUIT_VEGETABLE_ALTERNATIVE.

name: containerTypeCode
definition: The container in which the alcohol product has undergone a specific process. Example: Bourbon, Beer, Sherry Butt, Pin (Cask).

name: packagingComponentDescription
definition: Part of packaging that can be separated by hand or by using simple physical means (EN 13427, ISO/DIS 18601), for example a packaging film.

name: productYield
definition: Product quantity after preparation.

name: lightBulbFilamentTypeCode
definition: The type of filament used in the light bulb.  A filament is the threadlike conductor, often of tungsten, in the bulb that is heated to incandescence by the passage of current.

name: importClassificationTypeCode
definition: Imports and exports of trade items typically require classification codes to determine appropriate duties and tariffs. Values include Netherlands Import Code, Harmonized Commodity Description and Coding System, Customs Tariff and INTRASTAT Code, Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States, INTRASTAT Combined Nomenclature, Tarif Intégré de la Communauté

name: audioVisualMediaItemContributorTypeCode
definition: A code identifying the type of contributor to media content for example artist, producer, director.

name: authorisationDateTime
definition: First day on which the item will be authorised for sale to a location.

name: lightBulbWarmUpTime
definition: Indicates the maximum time in seconds the light bulb is warmed up to 60% of the full light output.

name: isTradeItemShippedInMultipleContainers
definition: Indicates that more than one box is to be delivered when the trade item is ordered.

name: documentActionCode
definition: Code specifying the action to be taken in the system of the recipient using the information in the document.

name: acidificationMeasurementReferenceSubstanceDescription
definition: The reference substance description used to represent the potential to acidify ecosystems.

name: registrationAgency
definition: An agency that issues registration numbers for any item or substance for example a chemical that is contained within the product.

name: recommendedFrequencyOfFeeding
definition: How frequently it is recommended to feed an animal the quantity of feed within a time period for the specified feed life-stage. Examples: 2 feedings per day,  maximum 2 chew sticks  and/or 2 portions per day.

name: isTradeItemADisplayUnit
definition: An indicator whether or not a trade item is or could be used as a display unit. A display unit is intended to be shipped to a store without being split at a distribution centre or similar party and is intended to be displayed in a retail store either on a shelf or on the shop floor.

name: declaredPower
definition: The declared power of a light bulb defines how much electricity the bulb can transform into light and heat over a given amount of time. If left on for one hour, a 25 Watt light bulb will use 25 Watt-hours (Wh) of energy.

name: languageCode
definition: A code representing the language used in the description.

name: storageCompatibilityCode
definition: A storage compatibilities expressed as a code.

name: noncreditableGrainDescription
definition: A descriptive term to describe the non creditable grain contained in the item.  This value must be supplied when non-creditable grains are present in the trade item.  In the US, this description should be from the Food Buying Guide.

name: countrySubdivisionCode
definition: The country subdivision in which a processing or other activity has been performed for example processing, bottling, manufacturing.

name: additionalCameraAngleCode
definition: An additional camera angle used to take a picture of the trade item for example ZOOM_VIEW. If this attribute is not populated, the assumption is a full trade item view. Uses FileCameraPerspectiveCode code list.

name: avpList
definition: <font color="#ff0000">Attribute value pair information.</font>

name: propertyCode
definition: A property of  a classification of an item expressed as a code.

name: relevantSupportingSubstanceHazardousDocumentation
definition: This is a certificate of compliance with relevant legislation. So the metric is a simple yes qualified with supporting documentation or a no.

name: hatTypeCode
definition: A code indicating the form or style of a hat.

name: chemicalPropertyName
definition: A characteristic of a chemical substance expressed as a name for example radionuclide.

name: audioVisualMediaDateTime
definition: The date for audio or visual media products for example release date.

name: actionNeeded
definition: Identifies the type of action the data source needs to take in order to resolve the data recipient's issue.

name: creditableIngredientAmountPerRawPortion
definition: The ounces per portion value of the raw creditable fruit or vegetable ingredient contained in the trade item as specified on the Product Formulation Statement and defined by the requirements, rules and regulations set forth by the applicable Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body.

name: bracketRangeQualifierCode
definition: Specifies whether the bracket range is based upon an amount, a measurement or another quantity

name: compulsoryAdditionalLabelInformation
definition: The legally required/compulsory additional label information as stated on the product packaging or label.

name: physiochemicalCharacteristicReferenceValue
definition: The measured value of the physiochemical characteristic or a value which results of several tests during the production process.

name: languageCode
definition: A code representing the language used in the description.

name: haveYouMinimizedHazardousSubstance
definition: Meeting the requirements of EN 13428 or ISO 18602 on heavy metals and dangerous/hazardous substances.

name: packagingShapeCode
definition: A code depicting the shape of a package for example cone.

name: packagingWeightReductionProtocolName
definition:
The protocol name that the calculation is based on. 
  (i.e.  packaging weight reduction should be calculated according to the protocol stipulated in GPPS 2.0)

name: regulatoryAgency
definition: The required information is the name of the specific entity in charge of issuing the permit to a company.

name: height
definition: The height of the unit load, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard, including the shipping platform unless it is excluded according to the platformTypeCode chosen.

name: fileEffectiveStartDateTime
definition: The date upon which the target of this external link begins to be effective for use.

name: feedingAmount
definition: The amount of feed which is specified for the feed life-stage and qualified by the weight of animal being fed.

name: lethalDose50Basis
definition: The basis measurement for the measurement of a Lethal Dose for example 1 LT in the ratio 10 MG/1 LT.

name: partyEndEffectiveDate
definition: The date and time that the party is no longer active.

name: dutyFeeTaxTypeCode
definition: Identification of the type of duty or tax or fee applicable to the trade item. This will vary by target market.

name: maximumFeedingAmount
definition: The maximum amount of feed which is specified for the feed life-stage and qualified by the weight of animal being fed.

name: storageStateCode
definition: A code depicting that the referred product was previously frozen or not.

name: startDateTimeOfExclusivity
definition: The date and time at which a product starts to be exclusive to a trading partner.

name: contributorPlaceRegion
definition: Identifies a region with which a contributor is particularly associated

name: gpcCategoryCode
definition: Code specifying a product category according to the GS1 Global Product Classification (GPC) standard.

name: tradeItemDateOnPackagingFormatTypeCode
definition: A category of date formats for example calendar or ordinal date.

name: professionalAffiliation
definition: An organisation to which a contributor to the product was affiliated at the time of its creation

name: packagingMaterialDescription
definition: A description of the packaging material.

name: minimumToleranceTemperature
definition: The minimum temperature at which the item is still usable. The tolerated temperature indicates that the temperature of the trade item should never fall below the minimum temperature.

name: aquaticEutrophicationReferenceSubstanceDescription
definition: The reference substance used to represent aquatic eutrophication potential.

name: targetHairTypeCode
definition: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the hair type for which the product is intended.

name: usageColourDescription
definition: A description of the usage of colour(s) the trade item offers such as pens, markers, ink pads, printer cartridges and other implements that provide color.  Examples include black, white.

name: multipleContainerQuantity
definition: The quantity of containers when the complete trade item is packed in multiple containers. If all components are packed together into one item this attribute is not used. For example: 3 boxes = 1st box  has 1 table,  2 more boxes with 2 chairs each, this attribute would contain the value 3.

name: catchDateTime
definition: The date of the catch within the EDI and/or Information at the label distributed with the product for information of any single lot of fresh fish and seafood product. Format (YYYYMMDD) as a specification with time stamp is not required in the current EU Regulation.  This required attribute will help the global retail industry to fulfill the EU requirements for a common fisheries policy. The data is required by the supply chain participant from source to end consumer.

name: itemAuthorisationStatusReason
definition: Additional details associated with the item authorisation status.

name: codeListVersion
definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: totalPortionWeightAsPurchased
definition: The total portion weight of the trade item as purchased.  This value(s) is as noted on the Product Formulation Statement and expressed in at least one measurement.

name: toxicityMeasurementProtocolDescription
definition: The description of the protocol used for the measurement.

name: salesRightsTypeCode
definition: Identifies the type of sales right or exclusion which applies in the territories which are associated with it. Mandatory in each occurrence of the <SalesRights> composite, and non-repeating. Values include: for sale with exclusive rights, for sale with non-exclusive rights, not for sale.

name: containerShapeCode
definition: The shape of the container used in a specific process for an alcohol product. Example: Firkin, Hogshead.

name: returnableAssetOwnerId
definition: The GLN of the owner of a returnable asset.

name: nutrientBasisQuantityDescription
definition: Additional free text information needed to correctly express nutrient basis quantity for example per bottle (100 ml).

name: conditionValueBasisQuantity
definition: The base amount used for a condition in the case or a rate for example $10 per '100' yards where 100 yards is the value basis.

name: chemicalPropertyCode
definition: A characteristic of a chemical substance expressed as a code.

name: gameFormatCode
definition: Code that identifies the electronic environment or system needed to use the electronic game. For example X-Box, Game Cube, PS2.

name: fileFeeDescription
definition: A description of the fees that are applicable to use of the digital asset.  This attribute may be a list of actual fees, a description of the fee structure, or contact information to find out the fees.

name: econtentTradeItemStatement
definition: A free text field providing additional information relating to the trade item. This is specifically addressing ecommerce content for consumers.

name: specialScenarioCode
definition: A specialised price synchronisation scenario that may be prevalent in a certain target market based on regional business practices or regulations. This attribute is used to trigger special processing by the data source and/or data recipient based on the needs of this scenario. This attribute uses the PriceSynchronisationSpecialScenarioCodeList.

name: microbiologicalOrganismMaximumValuePrecisionCode
definition: The measurement precision used for the measurement of the organism maximum value for example UNDETECTABLE.

name: editionStatement
definition: A short free-text description of a version or edition. Optional and non-repeating. When used, an <EditionStatement> must be complete in itself, ie it should not be treated as merely supplementary to an <EditionType> or an <EditionNumber>. An <EditionStatement> should be strictly limited to describing features of the content of the edition, and should not include aspects such as rights or market restrictions.

name: goodsPickupLeadTime

definition: Standard phrases assigned to a hazard class and category that describe the nature of the hazard for example H200.

name: protectiveEquipmentStatusCode
definition: A code determining whether the protective equipment is recommended or required.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: descriptionShort
definition: A free form short length description of the trade item that can be used to identify the trade item at point of sale.

name: consumerProductVariantDescription
definition: Free text field describing the Consumer Product Variant change/difference.

name: netContent
definition: The amount of the trade item contained by a package, usually as claimed on the label. For example, Water 750ml - net content = "750 MLT" ; 20 count pack of diapers, net content = "20 ea.". In case of multi-pack, indicates the net content of the total trade item. For fixed value trade items use the value claimed on the package, to avoid variable fill rate issue that arises with some trade item which are sold by volume or weight, and whose actual content may vary slightly from batch to batch. In case of variable quantity trade items, indicates the average quantity.

name: runModeCode
definition: The functional mode of a device expressed as a code for example ON, SLEEP or STANDBY. Run modes are defined by various guidelines for example the energy star guideline.

name: packagingMaterialDescription
definition: A description of the packaging material.

name: containerMaterialCode
definition: The material of the container used in a specific process for an alcohol product. Example: American White Oak (Quercus Alba), Stainless Steel.

name: nutritionalProgramStatusCode
definition: A code specifying the status of the brand or product with the nutritional program. Example: REGISTERED - the brand of a product is registered for Nutri-Score at the French Health Ministry.

name: contextIdentification
definition: <font color="#0f0f0f">The unique identifier established for the context managed by GS1</font><font color="#ff0000">.</font>

name: colourTintCode
definition: Indicates the tint or shade code of the product colour.

name: healthcareItemUsageAgeDescription
definition: Note: This attribute is being deprecated in a future release. Use targetConsumerAge from TargetConsumer class in MarketingInformationModule. Additional information regarding the usage age for a healthcare item for example "This product is not indicated for use in children under 6 years of age unless it is advised by a physician."

name: fileFormatName
definition: The name of the file format. Examples: PDF; JPEG; BMP

name: depth
definition: The depth of the trade item, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard. If the trade item is a unit load, include the shipping platform unless it is excluded according to the platformTypeCode chosen.

name: alcoholBeverageAge
definition: A value to provide the basic type of alcohol beverage product, for example- Spirit-Bourbon, Beer-German Bock, Still Wine-Ice Wine.

name: errorDateTime
definition: Point in time at which an error occurred.

name: gpcCategoryDefinition
definition: A GS1 supplied definition associated with the specified Global Product Classification (GPC) category code.

name: awardPrizeYear
definition: The year in which a prize or award was given.

name: plumbingHVACConnectionCode
definition: A code determining the connection point on the trade item that the plumbing connection type refers to. This code is determined by standards established by the plumbing HVAC connection agency.

name: avpList
definition: Attribute value pair information.

name: allergenSpecificationName
definition: Free text field containing the name and version of the regulation or standard that contains the definition of the allergen.

name: fileCampaignDescription
definition: A reference to a specific communication project to which the digital asset is associated, such as the Back To School Campaign. A campaign is a marketing term used to describe the event, sale, promotion, or other program for which this digital asset is designed to be part.

name: isTradeItemUDIDILevel
definition: An indicator used in the context of medical device trade item hierarchies. It signifies that the identifier (GTIN) of the trade item is the access key to the device's record in Unique Device Identification Databases.

name: householdCleaningProductTypeCode
definition: A code to differentiate household cleaning products from one another. The codes include, but are not limited to, the room the product is to be used in, the surfaces it's intended to clean, or the type of substance the product is meant to eliminate.

name: prohibitedForTransportationReason
definition: The reason that something is prohibited for transportation using a specific mode as a description.

name: massEquivalentSubstanceCodeReference
definition: The substance code related to the mass equivalent code.

name: visibleLight
definition: Total quantity of visible light emitted by a light source for example 1200 LUM.

name: isPartyActive
definition: A Boolean field used to express whether the party is active or inactive.

name: microbiologicalOrganismWarningValuePrecisionCode
definition: A code specifying the precision of the measurement of the organism warning value for example EXACT.

name: packagingWeight
definition: The weight and identity of a packaging constituent, component or system which changes hands in the supply chain.

name: drugSideEffectsAndWarnings
definition: Information to the side effects of the drug or supplement. This may be pre-labeled on the product or need to be labeled per target market regulations.  Examples include  Could make you drowsy, Do not operate machinery, Do not take if you are pregnant, etc.

name: lightBeamTypeCode
definition: The code that specifies the type of light beam emitted by a light bulb.

name: codeListNameCode
definition: The code list qualifying the temporary attribute for example MEASUREMENT_CODE.

name: propertyInteger
definition: A property of  a classification of an item expressed as an integer.

name: orderSizingFactor
definition: A trade item specification other than gross, net weight, or cubic feet for a line trade item or a transaction, used for order sizing and pricing purposes. For example, factors may be used to cube a truck, reflecting different weights, and dimensions of trade item.

name: cumulativeEnergyDemandReferenceSubstanceCode
definition: The reference substance used to represent cumulative energy demand.

name: physiochemicalCharacteristicWarningValuePrecisionCode
definition: A code specifying the precision of the warning value of the physiochemical characteristic for example EXACT.

name: tradeItemOperatingEnvironment
definition: The physical area(s) in which the manufacturer has designed the unit to be operated or installed for example underground, underwater, inside, outside etc.

name: processCapabilityCode
definition: A code representing a process that the party is capable of performing for example trade item synchronisation.

name: regulationCommunityLevelCode
definition: The type of territory the regulation is issued by for example a nation or territory considered as an organized political community under a government. Examples include; UNION, MUNICIPALITY, PROVENCE_OR_STATE.

name: spongeScourerTypeCode
definition: A descriptive code differentiating cleaning sponges or scourers from one another.

name: tradeItemPriceTypeCode
definition: The type of price for the item for example bulk price.

name: pegVertical
definition: Used to indicate the vertical distance of a peg hole measured from the bottom edge of the trade item to the top of the peg hole. Peg holes are inserted when the trade item is displayed on a pegboard.   Example: "2 INH." Information is required if the trade item is displayed on a peg board.

name: allowanceChargeTypeCode
definition: The identification of an allowance charge selected from a predefined list.

name: aquaticEutrophicationReferenceSubstanceCode
definition: The reference substance used to represent aquatic eutrophication potential.

name: availableLanguageCode
definition: The available languages used to interface with the consumer.

name: nutritionalProgramIngredientTypeCode
definition: Allows to identify the groups of main ingredients contained in the product to better highlight them for the consumer.

name: closureOrFastenerLocation
definition: The location on the trade item of the zipper, snap, button, etc.

name: registrationEndDateTime
definition: The last date that the registration number is valid.

name: processCapabilityEffectiveStartDateTime
definition: The date at which the registration of a process capability is effective

name: titleTypeCode
definition: Indicates the type of a title.

name: displayPanelBacklightType
definition: The backlighting utilized in the panel.  Most commonly Cold Cathode Fluorescent Lamps (CCFLs) or Light Emitting Diodes (LEDs).

name: massEquivalentCode
definition: The type of mass equivalent being measured.

name: maximumToleranceTemperature
definition: The maximum temperature at which the item is still usable. The tolerated temperature indicates that the temperature of the trade item should never rise above the maximum temperature.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: tradeItemCompositionDepth
definition: The number of child-items that are packaged from front to back in a trade unit. This information is used in the space process, especially when allocating whole Trade Units (intermediate) into the shelf.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: paymentDueBasisTypeCode
definition: The basis type on which the payment is due. For example,  RECEIPT_OF_GOODS.

name: footwearStyleCode
definition: A code indicating the form, construction, usage, style, or special purpose of a shoe.

name: countryCode
definition: The country in which a processing or other activity has been performed for example processing, bottling, manufacturing.

name: productActivityTypeCode
definition: A code depicting the type of activity being performed on a trade item for example ASSEMBLY, BOTTLING. LAST_PROCESSING.

name: flashPointTestMethodCode
definition: The test method used to determine the flash point temperature for example closed cup.

name: animalNutritionalClaim
definition: Free text field for any additional nutritional claims in relations to animal feed.

name: zoomTimesFactor
definition: The distance (how far or close) the zoom is capable of for example 2, 10.5, 100.

name: threadDenier
definition: Denier is a measurement for fabric and threads. It is the mass in grams per 9,000 meters (9 kilometres) of the fibre/thread. The denier is based on a natural reference: a single strand of silk is approximately one denier; a 9000-meter strand of silk weighs about one gram (1 denier = 1 g / 9000 m).

name: isRadioFrequencyIDOnPackaging
definition: Indicates that the packaging of the trade item is tagged with a Radio Frequency ID.

name: areBatteriesIncluded
definition: Indicates if batteries are either included or not included with the trade item.

name: hairProductFunctionOrTreatmentCode
definition: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify different functions of the product and other treatments.

name: languageCode
definition: A code representing the language used in the description.

name: consumerUsageInstructions
definition: Expresses in text the consumer usage instructions of a product which are normally held on the label or accompanying the product. This information may or may not be labeled on the pack. Instructions may refer to a the how the consumer is to use the product, This does not include storage, food preparations, and drug dosage and preparation instructions.

name: contributorPlaceTypeCode
definition: Identifies a region with which a contributor is particularly associated

name: platformTermsAndConditionsCode
definition: Indicates if the pallet in the prescribed pallet configuration is rented, exchangeable, against deposit or one way (not reusable).

name: additionalPartyIdentification
definition: Identification of a party by use of a code other than the Global Location Number.

name: geneticallyModifiedDeclarationCode
definition: A statement of the presence or absence of genetically modified protein or DNA.

name: width
definition: The width of the unit load, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard, including the shipping platform unless it is excluded according to the platformTypeCode chosen.

name: boilingPoint
definition: The temperature of a liquid at which its vapour pressure is equal to or very slightly greater than the atmospheric pressure of the environment. Note: (For water at sea level it is 100°C (212°F).

name: contributorDate
definition: The date specified that is associated with the person or organization identified as a contributor.

name: healthcareItemMaximumUsageAge
definition: Note: This attribute is being deprecated in a future release. Use targetConsumerUsageTypeCode with the value AGE and targetConsumerMaximumUsage from TargetConsumerUsage class in MarketingInformationModule. The maximum age to which the healthcare item may be used. For example 6 MON or 18 ANN.

name: extentTypeCode
definition: An ONIX code which identifies the type of extent carried in the composite, eg running time for an audio or video product. Mandatory in each occurrence of the <Extent> composite, and non-repeating. From Issue 9 of the code lists, an extended set of values for <ExtentType> has been defined to allow more accurate description of pagination.

name: partyReceivingPrivateData
definition: Party, which is authorized to view, use, download the data provided by a Data Source.

name: criteriaObjectValue
definition: The exact value to be applied in the search.  In the following Search Criteria, the GLN value of “0012345000065” is the Object Value:  “Party, GLN EQUAL_TO 0614141000012”

name: selfTimerDelay
definition: The amount of time the timer on a camera runs before the mechanism triggers the action. Example 2 seconds, 10 seconds, Custom.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: packagingLabellingCoveragePercentage
definition: Percentage of print/label and/or varnish coverage on the surface of the packaging.

name: batteryTechnologyTypeCode
definition: The type of battery family (e.g. Lithium, NiMH) of batteries used by the product.

name: doesTradeItemCompositionIncludeLatex
definition: Identifies if any of the trade item’s components or pieces contain latex.

name: doesPackagingRecoveryRateTypeCodeMeetTheStandard
definition: Determine if the packaging recovery rate meet the standard.

name: genus
definition: A taxonomic category ranking below a family and above a species and generally consisting of a group of species exhibiting similar characteristics. In taxonomic nomenclature the genus name is used, either alone or followed by a Latin adjective or epithet, to form the name of a species.

name: priceAttributeName
definition: Name of the attribute in the Price Synchronization message.

name: chemicalPropertyTypeCode
definition: The type of chemical property being described expressed as a code such as TOXICITY.

name: epubUsageLimit
definition: Specifies a quantitative limit on a particular type of usage of a digital product.

name: partyReference
definition: The identifier of the party registered at the global registry.

name: isReprocessedSingleUseDevice
definition: Indication the device is a single use device which has been Reprocessed. Rules for reprocessing are governed by local market regulations.

name: waterSolubilityTypeCode
definition: Water solubility is defined as a code indicating solubility in respect to water. Solubility is the ability of a given substance to dissolve in a solvent.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: ingredientStrengthBasis
definition: The basis amount for an ingredient strength for example 1000 millilitres in the case of 400 milligrams per 1000 millilitres.

name: annexXVIintendedPurposeTypeCode
definition: All intended purposes other than for medical uses which apply to the product (EUDAMED Annex XVI).

name: warrantyEffectiveDateType
definition: The type of date associated with the warranty trade item usually expressed as an event date for the item for example date of purchase, date of manufacture or date of delivery.

name: isTradeItemREACHRelevant
definition: An indicator that the trade item may have ingredients that subject it to REACH.

name: dangerousGoodsSubsidiaryClass
definition: Local dangerous goods regulations may allow for a subsidiary or secondary dangerous goods class number to be associated with the first or primary dangerous goods class number. Depending on local regulations, a subsidiary class number may be shown in parentheses immediately after the first or primary dangerous goods class number.

name: consumerWarningDescription
definition: A description associated with a specific warning type for example if the consumerWarningTypeCode is AGE, the consumerWarningDescription would be "for ages 15 and over".

name: nutrientRelevantDataProvidedDateTime
definition: The date upon which the isNutrientRelevantDataProvided indicator was last updated.

name: publicationDateTypeCode
definition: An ONIX code indicating the significance of the date in relation to the text content. Mandatory in each occurrence of the composite, and non-repeating. In ONIX this is the and utilizes list 155.

name: nonfoodIngredientDefinition
definition: A definition associated with the value in the nonfoodIngredientName.  The definition should explain to the end user what the nonfood ingredient is.

name: allowanceOrChargeType
definition: Code specifying whether this is an allowance or a charge.

name: xPath
definition: The XPath representing a specific attribute in an XML message or data base for example RegistryParty/isPartyActive.

name: allowanceChargeDescription
definition: A text explanation of the allowance or charge.

name: alcoholBeverageProductionMethodTypeCode
definition: A method by which an alcohol beverage product has been produced. Example: Methode Traditionnelle, Added Carbonization, Chamenoise.

name: isUniversalWaste
definition: Indicates if a product can be considered universal waste. Universal waste is defined as "are wastes that do not meet the regulatory definition of hazardous waste, but are managed under special, tailored regulations"

name: languageCode
definition: A code representing the language used in the description.

name: isDeviceExemptFromImplantObligations
definition: Indication the medical device is exempted from specific obligations imposed on implantable devices by the regulation. Refer to EU MDR Article 18/3 Implant Card and Information to be supplied to the patient with an implanted device.

name: height
definition: The height of the trade item, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard. If the trade item is a unit load, include the shipping platform unless it is excluded according to the platformTypeCode chosen.

name: shortSynopsis
definition: A short text that describes the plot of a film

name: maximumValue
definition: Specifies the upper limit of the string range.

name: remoteControlTypeCode
definition: The type of remote control functionality available with a unit expressed as a code.

name: payPerViewWindow
definition: The number of days of the pay per view window. The pay per view window is the timeframe when a film is available as pay per view on a cable TV channel.

name: containerProcessTypeCode
definition: The process which is undertaken in a specific container for an alcohol product. Example: Maturation-Primary, Maturation-Secondary, Finishing.

name: orderFrom
definition: The location that the item can be ordered from according to the condition synchronised.

name: controlledSubstanceAmount
definition: The numeric amount of a specific substance the item contains that is regulated under  law as narcotics, stimulants, depressants, hallucinogens, anabolic steroids, and chemicals used in the illicit production of controlled substances

name: codeListVersion
definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

name: testSpeciesCode
definition: A description of any species of animal that was used for determining LC and LD other than the norm.

name: codeListVersion
definition: The version of the code list qualifying the temporary attribute.

name: fileCompressionType
definition: A description of the compression method used to reduce the file size stored at the link. This information is used to aid the user in choosing the correct program to extract the file. Examples include Quick Time, Real Player, mpg, WinZip, etc.

name: freshWaterEcotoxicityReferenceSubstanceDescription
definition: The reference substance description used to represent freshwater ecotoxicity.

name: runTimeMinutes
definition: The length of a media item expressed in minutes.

name: tradeItemExclusiveSellingLocationCode
definition: A code identifying the kind of selling location(s) in which the product can be sold for example BOAT .  This can apply to both physical and digital locations.

name: colourTemperature
definition: Colour temperature is a way to describe the light appearance provided by a light bulb for example 2700 KEL.

name: isIngredientEmphasised
definition: Denotes that the ingredient should have it's text emphasised.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: packagingMaterialClassificationCodeReference
definition: Identifies the packing material classification used in each packaging component. It is assumed that a packaging material classification would be a broader material grouping that other packaging materials would fit under as classified by a specific agency.

name: packagingMaterialCompositionQuantity
definition: The quantity of the packaging material of the trade item. Can be weight, volume or surface, can vary by country.

name: globalModelNumber
definition: The GS1 Global Model Number (GMN) is the GS1 identification key used to identify a product model or product family based on attributes common to the model or family as defined by industry or regulation. This GS1 identification key, once assigned to one product model or product family, SHALL NOT be reissued to another. The GMN SHALL NOT be used to identify a trade item.

name: contentDescription
definition: Free form description of the content of the file

name: packagingLabellingTypeCode
definition: The type of text coverage of a packaging, e.g. Label, Printed on packaging.

name: microbiologicalOrganismMethodOfAnalysisCode
definition: Method of analysis used to determine quantity of the specified microbiological organism (E.g. probiotic live microbe) in the product. Example: Aerobic plate count, Flow cytometry.

name: apparelDetailPlacementCode
definition: A code indicating the location of the detail application on a product.

name: chemicalIngredientOrganisation
definition: An organization managing a chemical ingredient identification scheme.

name: doesTradeItemContainAnimalTissue
definition: Indication the product has presence of animal tissues or cells or their derivates.

name: proximoCutOffDay
definition: The day of the month the payment becomes due.

name: dataRecipient
definition: Party, which is authorized to view, use, download a set of Master Data provided by a Data Source.

name: protectiveEquipmentBodyAreaCode
definition: A code determining the part of the body the protective equipment is meant to protect for example EYE

name: nominalInsideDiameter
definition: The measurement of the nominal (not the exact measurement) inside diameter of the plumbing connection point of the trade item.

name: awardPrizeJury
definition: Free text listing members of the jury that awarded the prize.

name: extinguishingMediaDescription
definition: A description of any substance that can be used to extinguish a fire, carbon dioxide, water etc in relation to any hazardous materials for example those regulated by ADR (European Agreement concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road).

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: microbiologicalOrganismMaximumValue
definition: Maximum allowable Colony Forming Units (CFU) of the microbiological organism per weight or volume.

name: audienceRangeValue1
definition: A value indicating an exact position within a range, or the upper or lower end of a range.

name: tradeItemFinishDescription
definition: An attribute which defines the outer surface/appearance of the product.

name: sweetnessLevelOfAlcoholicBeverageCode
definition: Indicates the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the sweetness of the alcoholic beverage. These are sometimes placed on a label. In some markets, the term is based on the amount of sugar content according to local regulation.

name: inBoxCubeDimension
definition: The dimensions of an imaginary cube which can be drawn around the trade item as defined in the formula of H X W X D (The linear dimensions multiplied to get a cubic result). This only applies to In-box dimensions. Level of Hierarchy applied to-  All.  Example- Bag of cabbage, Bag of Flour, Broom, Ham Case of Beer.

name: countryCode
definition: The country in which a processing or other activity has been performed for example processing, bottling, manufacturing.

name: discountAmount
definition: The deduction represented as an amount.

name: certificationEffectiveStartDateTime
definition: The date and time upon which the certification is effective.

name: tradeItemSustainabilityStatement
definition: The statement that describes how a trade item is produced in a way that can be maintained into the future without harming the environment. This may refer to marketing facing information that is relevant to the consumer who is concerned with sustainability.

name: creditableGrainGroupCode
definition: The code assigned by the Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body indicating to which exhibit group the trade item belongs.  This code specifics set the formulas and calculations used to determine the grain equivalents for the trade item.

name: audienceRangeValue2
definition: A value indicating the upper end of a range.

name: keyNames
definition: Part of a structured name of a person who contributed to the creation of the product: key name(s), i.e. the name elements normally used to open an entry in an alphabetical list, e.g. ‘Smith’ or ‘Garcia Marquez’ or ‘Madonna’ or ‘Francis de Sales’ (in Saint Francis de Sales).

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: sequenceNumber
definition: A number used to indicate the order in which the allowances or charges are to be calculated.

name: alcoholBeverageDistilledFromCode
definition: The main ingredient(s) from which the alcohol product has been distilled. Example: Rye, Potato, Sugar Cane.

name: audienceDescription
definition: Free text describing the audience for which a product is intended. Optional and non-repeating.

name: specificGravityLowerValue
definition: The lower value in a range of specific gravity.

name: additionalSDSInformation
definition: A description field for other information regarding the MSDS that is not in the other sections. For example, additional contact information, or sustainability statement, other information.

name: placementOfDivider
definition: Indicates layer number that the dividers are found.  Layer dividers are always counted starting at the uppermost layer (top to bottom) or leftmost divider (Left to right).  For example “3”, “5” would mean that the 2 dividers are located on the 3rd and 5th layer counting always from the top to bottom.

name: totalQuantityOfNextLowerLevelTradeItem
definition: This represents the Total quantity of next lower level trade items that this trade item contains.

name: contributorPlaceCountry
definition: A code identifying a country with which a contributor is particularly associated.

name: packagingRecycledContentDescription
definition: The description of recycled content that is being measured for.

name: packagingRecoveryRateTypeCode
definition: A code determining the type of recovery applicable to the packaging.

name: chemicalIngredientConcentrationMeasurementPrecision
definition: The measurement precision used to determine the concentration of a chemical ingredient for example EXACT.

name: stackingWeightMaximum
definition: The maximum admissible weight that can be stacked on the trade item. This uses a measurement consisting of a unit of measure and a value. This will be used for transport or storage to allow user to know by weight how to stack different trade item one on top of the other.

name: chemicalIngredientIdentification
definition: A unique number to identify a chemical used to cross reference regulated lists of chemicals for example CAS number.

name: additionalTradeItemClassificationVersion
definition: The identification of a release of a particular product classification.

name: sender
definition: The party sending the query.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: tradeItemPrice
definition: Provides the trade item price value.

name: jewelryStyleCode
definition: A code indicating the intended use and general value  of the materials used in a piece of jewelry.

name: gHSSignalWordsCode
definition:
Words such as "Danger" or "Warning" used to emphasize hazards and indicate the relative level of severity of the hazard. 
For GHS these are assigned to a GHS hazard class and category. Some lower level hazard categories do not use signal words.

name: partyDataPool
definition: The Global Location Number of the data pool responsible for registering the party record in the GS1 Global Registry.

name: containedAlternativeProteinPercent
definition: The percent of alternative protein as provided in the item. In the US this is noted on the Alternate Protein Product (APP) documentation.

name: regulationLevelCodeReference
definition: An external code associated with a specific warning type and possibly a description that helps recipients identify items of similar levels of warnings, that cannot be obtained from a description. The information provided in this attribute may come from a specific article in the full Regulation. For examples : - if the regulationTypeCode is "SMALL_PARTS" the regulationLevelCodeReference would be “Level 5” with codeDescription “Not for ages under 3” - if the regulationTypeCode is "BIOCIDE_REGULATION" the regulationLevelCodeReference would be “PT1” with codeDescription “Human hygiene”

name: allowanceChargeAmount
definition: Amount of allowance or charge applicable.

name: tradeItemLicenseOwnerGLN
definition: The GLN of the owner of the licensed product that is allowing the trading partner to use their licensed name and/or images.

name: regulatoryAct
definition: The name given to the requirement assigned by the regulatory agency.

name: isBioengineeredDeclarationClaimRelevantDataProvided
definition: All Bioengineered Declaration Claim Information is populated for those values which are relevant or required to be populated on the product label or label equivalent.  values not populated are not relevant or not required to be populated on the product label by local regulations.

name: grossWeight
definition: Used to identify the gross weight of the trade item. The gross weight includes all packaging materials of the trade item. At pallet level the trade item-GrossWeight includes the weight of the pallet itself. For example, "200 grm", value - total pounds, total grams, etc. Has to be asso-ciated with a valid UOM.

name: tradeItemLicenseTitle
definition: The title of the licensed trademark asset that is used on the trade item.

name: shippingRegulationException
definition: A description of any reasons for excluding a trade item or component from a hazardous regulation for a mode of transportation.

name: allergenRelevantDataProvidedDateTime
definition: The date upon which the isAllergenRelevantDataProvided indicator was last updated.

name: shippingQuantityMinimum
definition: The minimum total quantity of this trade item that can be shipped.

name: contentDateRoleTypeCode
definition: Indicates the significance of the date in relation to the text content.

name: neckwearTypeCode
definition: A code indicating the shape or use of the neckwear.

name: compulsoryAdditionalLabelInformationTypeCode
definition: The code indicating the type of the legally required/compulsory additional information that is stated on the product packaging label.

name: complementAddress
definition:
The complement address expressed as a free form text. The complement address is printed on paper as additional lines below the street address. For example, an industrial zone or apartment number.
Required in case the PD Organisation link is provided (Product Designer Link relates to an Organisation)

name: alcoholicPermissionLevel
definition: Indication of a Permission level for alcoholic products dependent on the product classification. The permission level codes should reflect those of the target market.

name: alternativeName
definition: It may be used to send a pseudonym as well as a real name, where both names are on the product, eg to handle such cases as ‘Ian Rankin writing as Jack Harvey’; or to send an authority-controlled form of a name; or to identify the real name of the contributor where the book is written under a pseudonym (and the real identity need not be kept private). Note that in all cases, the primary name is that used on the product, and the alternative name merely provides additional information.

name: acidificationMeasurementProtocolCode
definition: The reference protocol used to represent the potential to acidify ecosystems.

name: targetOccasionOrTheme
definition: The particular target time, event, theme, or holiday for the product for example Mother's Day, baby shower, birthday, etc..

name: postalCode
definition: Text specifying the postal code for an address.

name: originOfWineCode
definition: Indicates the country, region and sub-region where the wine has been produced. The levels of origin required are sometimes regulated, therefore the values represent a variety that allows a recipient to choose which level is needed.

name: nonfoodIngredientOfConcernCode
definition: Specifies a non-food ingredient of concern for a trade item as a code.

name: fileRightsDescription
definition: The structure for Digital Rights Management (DRM) which is in place on the file. This could be ID and location of external Intellectual Property Management & Protection (IPMP) system for lookup of usage rights.  Presence of a value for this attribute signifies that the file uses a DRM.

name: tradeItemVariantStatement
definition: A complete statement describing the variant, that may comply with any regulatory requirements in a target market. Example for flavour: Barbecue with natural and artificial flavours.

name: chemicalRegulationName
definition: The name of a regulation managed by a regulatory agency designed to restrict the handling, use, disposal of chemical ingredients for example Right to Know or CERCLA.

name: gpcCategoryCode
definition: The GS1 provided code which identifies the Global Product Classification Attribute Value.

name: handlingInstructionsCodeReference
definition: Defines the information and processes needed to safely handle the trade item.

name: conditionActionCode
definition: A code assigned by the Information Provider to indicate to the Party Receiving Private Data, the reason for sending the price information contained within the specified segment within the Price Synchronization Message. The Party Receiving Private Data is able to use this code to determine the nature of the action associated with each condition within each condition segment. For example the addition of a new record, the modification of an existing record or the correction of an existing record.

name: copyrightOwnerIdentifierTypeCodeReference
definition: Identifies the scheme from which the value in the copyrightOwnerIdentifier attribute is taken.

name: facilitiesInStressedWaterAreaPercent
definition: Percent of facilities owned by a single operator located in an area identified as a stressed or scarce water resource area.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: compulsoryAdditionalLabelInformationTypeCode
definition: The code indicating the type of the legally required/compulsory additional information that is stated on the product packaging or label.

name: packagingGeneratedMaterialWaste
definition: The mass of material waste generated during the production and transport of packaging materials, packaging constituents, packaging components or packaging systems destined to final disposal, i.e. landfill or incineration without heat recovery.

name: stringAVP
definition: An attribute value pair that allows for a string.

name: codeListVersion
definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

name: dutyFeeTaxExemptPartyRoleCode
definition: The party role (e.g. CONSUMER) that is exempt from a specific tax, duty or fee.

name: personName
definition: The name of the individual that can be contacted to provide additional information

name: communityInvestmentRatio
definition: The value of investments made in community projects related to packaging such as recycling education programs or recycling infrastructure development over and above regulated requirements.

name: totalScreenArea
definition: The area of a television or monitor screen typically measured as viewable screen height by viewable screen width

name: isTradeItemRegulationCompliant
definition: The indicator specifying whether the product is compliant, not compliant or not applicable to the regulation associated with the Regulation Type Code.

name: marinePollutantTechnicalName
definition: The technical chemical name of any marine pollutant contained in the item or component.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: businessContextIdentification
definition: The unique identifier established for the context established by GS1.

name: packagingGeneratedMaterialWaste
definition: The mass of material waste generated during the production and transport of packaging materials, packaging constituents, packaging components or packaging systems destined to final disposal, i.e. landfill or incineration without heat recovery

name: reportableQuantityTechnicalName
definition: A recognized chemical name or microbiological name currently used in scientific and technical handbooks, journals, and texts for a chemical that exists in the Trade Item in quantity viewed as reportable according to a regulation for example US EPA.

name: corporateNameInverted
definition: The inverted name of a corporate body

name: materialTreatment
definition: Indicates how the material is treated for example natural (un-treated), painted, dyed, bleach, coloured, etc.

name: transportationModeRegulatoryAgency
definition: The agency requiring information based on a specific mode of transportation for example ADR, IATA, DOT, IMDG.

name: alcoholUnits
definition: The number of alcohol units contained in the product as defined by local target market regulations. May also be referred to as number of standard drinks in certain geographies. Used as a measure to quantify the actual alcoholic content within the product, in order to provide guidance on total alcohol consumption. Example: 500ml of 4.5 percent ABV beer is 2.5 alcohol units in the UK and 2.0 standard drinks in Australia.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: materialCode
definition: This element indicates the product material code that gives the composition of the trade item's first main material up to six material short codes that can be given in descend-ing order of their respective percentages.

name: partyAddress
definition: The address associated with the party. This could be the full company address.

name: packagingRecyclingProcessTypeCode
definition: The process the packaging could undertake for recyclable & sustainability programs. Examples COMPOSTABLE, ENERGY_RECOVERABLE, REUSABLE

name: packagingMaterialThickness
definition: The thickness of a packaging material.

name: isTradeItemABaseUnit
definition: An indicator identifying the trade item as the base unit level of the trade item hierarchy.

name: maximumPH
definition: The maximum range for PH.

name: filePrintHeight
definition: The number of pixels along the vertical axis of the image.

name: streetAddress
definition: The street address expressed as free form text. The street address is printed on paper as the first lines below the name. Some trading partners require the street address to be the street name and number in this attribute. Others require this attribute to be just the street name. In this case, the street number should be provided separately in the street number attribute, if required.

name: firstShipDateTime
definition: Indicates the earliest date that the trade item can be shipped. This is independent of any specific ship-from location.

name: animalNutrientMinimumPercentage
definition: Minimum guaranteed percentage of the specified nutrient contained in the trade item.

name: lowerExplosiveLimit
definition: The low end value expressed as a percent by volume that the mixture is still flammable.

name: epubTechnicalProtectionTypeCode
definition: Specifies whether a digital product has DRM or other technical protection features.

name: nonfoodIngredientStatement
definition: Information on the constituent ingredient make-up of the product as specified for non-food items.

name: timeOfApplicationCode
definition: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the time of product application.

name: avpList
definition: Attribute value pair information.

name: gs1TradeItemIdentificationKeyCode
definition: The Global Trade Item Number which is visible on the item or its packaging and can be used to identify a trade item.
