equipment), a government regulated agency that sets
guidelines for product not to contain certain hazardous
substances. The RoHS (restriction of the use of certain
hazardous substances) bans the placing on the EU market of new electrical and electronic equipment containing more than
agreed levels of lead, cadmium, mercury, hexavalent chromium, polybrominated biphenyl (PBB) and polybrominated diphenyl ether (PBDE) flame retardants.

name: isTradeItemUniversalWaste
definition:
Indicates if a product can be considered universal waste.
Universal waste is defined as “wastes that do meet the
regulatory definition of hazardous waste, but are managed under special, tailored regulations.

name: isTradeItemConsumerUpgradeableOrMaintainable
definition:
Indicates if a product can be easily upgraded or have parts
replaced by the consumer. For example, the ability to add
additional memory/storage capacity or access and replace
chargeable batteries.

name: doesManufacturerHaveTakeBackProgram
definition: Indicates if the manufacturer of the trade item offers any take back programs to consumers for the product to be reused, re-manufactured or recycled by the manufacturer.

name: physicalResourceUsageClassificationCodeReference
definition: A classification code value from a product classification scheme provided to drive required information for resource usage.

name: wasteAmount
definition: The amount of the components contained in the trade item that are covered by a waste directive for example WEEE.

name: wasteDirectiveApplianceType
definition: The category of electrical and electronic equipment containing components covered by a waste directive for example WEEE.

name: wasteDirectiveName
definition: The name of a waste directive for example WEEE.

name: wasteDirectiveRegistrationNumber
definition: A registration number for a trade item required by a waste directive (e.g. WEEE).

name: dangerousSubstanceHeatOfCombustion
definition: The amount of heat generated by the item should it catch on fire expressed as amount of energy per pound for example BTU’s (British Thermal Units) per pound.

name: dangerousSubstanceName
definition: The name of the type of dangerous substance contained in the trade item for example Butane.

name: dangerousSubstanceGasDensity
definition: The density of gas contained within the trade item. This can be used by the data receiver to determine the total stored amounts of gas within a storage facility in accordance with dangerous substance regulations.  Use appropriate measurement for example in Europe (grams per Cubic Centimetre).

name: dangerousSubstancesWaterSolubilityCode
definition: A code indicating the solubility or miscibility in respect with water. Solubility is the ability of a given substance to dissolve in a solvent. Miscibility is the property of liquids to mix in all proportions, forming a homogeneous solution.

name: isDangerousSubstance
definition: An indicator whether or not a trade item is classified and labelled as containing a dangerous substance.

name: flammableSubstanceMinimumPercent
definition: The minimum percentage of the flammable substance contained in the trade item.  This can be used by the data receiver to support determining total stored amounts within a storage facility in accordance with dangerous substance regulations.

name: flammableSubstanceMaximumPercent
definition: The maximum percentage of the flammable substance contained in the trade item. This can be used by the data receiver to support determining total stored amounts within a storage facility in accordance with dangerous substance regulations.

name: dangerousSubstancePhaseOfMatterCode
definition:
A set of qualitatively different states, depending on
temperature and pressure related physical properties. They are divided into solid, liquid,gaseous and mixed forms of the substance.

name: gpcCategoryCode
definition: Code specifying a product category according to the GS1 Global Product Classification (GPC) standard.

name: gpcCategoryName
definition: Name associated with the specified Global Product Classification (GPC) category code.

name: gpcAttributeTypeCode
definition: Code specifying the type of the Global Product Classification (GPC) attribute, for example 20000081 - Grape Variety.

name: gpcAttributeTypeName
definition: The GS1 provided text equivalent of the Global Product Classification Attribute Code.

name: additionalTradeItemClassificationPropertyCode
definition: Code assigned to aproperty of product for a classification.

name: additionalTradeItemClassificationPropertyDescription
definition: A description of a property of product for a specific classification for example Waterproof.

name: catalogueItemConfirmationStateCode
definition: Codelist for the 4 modes of data reflected by a Data Pool: Accepted, Rejected,Review and Synchronised.

name: recipientGLN
definition: The Party, which is authorized to view, use, and download a set of Master Data provided by a Data Source. Note this attribute is synonymous with dataRecipient but is in this case the party where the Catalogue Item Confirmation was generated from or on behalf of.

name: recipientDataPool
definition: A data pool that supports the functionality of the Data Recipient (Subscription, Confirmation, Search, Request for Notification, etc.)

name: confirmationStatusCode
definition: The CIC Confirmation Code must be of a type of code number that can be generated automatically by a computer system. The CIC Confirmation Code must be of a type of code number that may be generated by either the data recipient (and passed through the Datapool processes) or the data pool.

name: confirmationStatusCodeDescription
definition: Provides the code description that matches up with the Code that can possibly be generated automatically by a computer system. ; CIC01

name: additionalConfirmationStatusLongDescription
definition: Provides a way to communicate human entered information that may not be covered by the machine to machine codes and descriptions. ; CIC02

name: correctiveActionCode
definition: Provides the corrective action code to fix the issue that caused the problem.

name: expectedCorrectiveInformation
definition: Provides the expected corrective information via a human entered information that may not be covered by the machine to machine codes. ; CIC01

name: isReload
definition: The Boolean value within the request for notification process (True = currently on the notification list and False = initialload).

name: quantity
definition: Number of units required.

name: catalogueItemStateCode
definition: The four states are: Registered , Cancelled, In Progress and Discontinued .

name: cancelDateTime
definition: Date assigned by data source and stored in the source data pool reflecting the date the catalogue item was cancelled. This date will also be stored in the Registry.

name: discontinueDateTime
definition: Date assigned by data source and stored in the source data pool reflecting the date the catalogue item was discontinued. This date will also be stored in the Registry.

name: publishToGLN
definition: Within the registry context, information is published to a party, identified by the Global Location Number-- The globally unique EAN.UCC System identification number for physical, functional, or legal entities. The Global Location Number uses the EAN/UCC-13 Data Structure

name: dataRecipient
definition: Party, which is authorized to view, use, download a set of Master Data provided by a Data Source.

name: dataSource
definition: Entity that provides the global data synchronization network with Master Data. The Data Source is officially recognized as the owner of this data. For a given Item or Party, the source of data is responsible for permanent updates of the information under its responsibility.

name: gtin
definition: A particular Global trade item Number, a numerical value used to uniquely identify a trade item. A trade item is any trade item (trade item or service) upon which there is a need to retrieve pre-defined information and that may be planned, priced, ordered, delivered and or invoiced at any point in any supply chain.

name: recipientDataPool
definition: A data pool that supports the functionality of the Data Recipient (Subscription, Confirmation, Search, Request for Notification, etc.)

name: cancelDateTime
definition: Date assigned by data source and stored in the source data pool reflecting the date the catalogue item was cancelled. This date will also be stored in the Registry.

name: deletionDateTime
definition: Date assigned by data source and stored in the source data pool reflecting the date the catalogue item was flagged for deletion. This date will also be stored in the Registry.

name: discontinuedDateTime
definition: Date assigned by data source and stored in the source data pool reflecting the date the catalogue item was discontinued. This date will also be stored in the Registry.

name: lastChangedDateTime
definition: Date assigned by system indicating last time the information was changed. This date is generic and will be stored where assigned and will accompany every message.

name: registrationDateTime
definition: Date assigned by the registry of successful registration.

name: distributionMethodCode
definition: The mode by which the Information Provider and the Party Receiving Private Data have agreed at what point(s) in the supply chain the Information Provider makes the goods available to the Party Receiving Private Data.

name: priceActionCode
definition: A code assigned by the Information Provider to indicate to the Party Receiving Private Data, the reason for sending the price information contained within the specified segment within the Price Synchronization Message. The Party Receiving Private Data is able to use this code to determine the nature of the action associated with each price component within each price type segment. For example the addition of a new record, the modification of an existing record or the correction of an existing record.

name: priceTypeApplicationSequence
definition: The order in which the value associated with a price type is applied in the process of calculating the net invoice price.

name: priceTypeCode
definition: A code assigned to identify the kind or class of a price component.

name: priceTypeLastChangedDateTime
definition: Identifies a certain point in time where the segment was last modified.

name: alternateLocationGrouping
definition: A string of characters used to describe a cluster of business locations mutually defined by the Information Provider and the Party Receiving Private Data.

name: extension
definition: An extension point for an Item  Price Type.

name: invoiceIssuer
definition: The party who issues the invoice for the trade item according to the price synchronised.

name: isBulkUpdate
definition: Indicates that the update to the price type is for a full price list update. This update may include price increase, price decrease, unchanged prices or new prices. This price change is managed globally by the retailer.

name: orderFrom
definition: The location that the item can be ordered from according to the price synchronised

name: priceActionReason
definition: A code to indicate the justification or explanation as to why the action associated with each price component has occurred. All actions may have an associated reason.

name: priceTargetMarketSubdivision
definition: The code for country sub-division used to indicate the geo-political subdivision of the target market (=country).

name: priceTypeDescription
definition: Text used to provide an additional description of the price component.

name: shipFrom
definition: Identifies the origin location from where the goods will be shipped.

name: shipTo
definition: The location destination to which goods will be shipped.

name: suggestedUnitRetailPrice
definition: The retail (to consumer) price as suggested by the manufacturer. This is normally used to establish a proposed value for the trade item for marketing purposes. May or may not appear on the package.

name: dataRecipient
definition: The party receiving the private data (for example, retailer). This information is taken from the price synchronization header of the price message to which this confirmation is responding.

name: dataSource
definition: The information provider of the Price Synchronization message (for example, supplier). This is taken from the price synchronization header of the price message to which this confirmation is responding.

name: actionNeeded
definition: Identifies the type of action the data source needs to take in order to resolve the data recipient's issue.

name: confirmationStatusReasonCode
definition: Identifies the type issue the data recipient has with the value communicated in the attribute name.

name: priceAttributeName
definition: Name of the attribute in the Price Synchronization message.

name: priceAttributeValue
definition: Value sent in the price synchronisation message that is associated with the attribute name.

name: codeListAgencyCode
definition: A code representing the agency which manages the code list for example 5 for ISO.

name: codeListURI
definition: A string that refers to the location of the code list which provides the code value.

name: codeListVersion
definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

name: languageCode

name: currencyCode
definition: A code representing the currency of a particular country or group of countries.

definition: Measurement of the distance between the front and the back.

name: height
definition: The vertical dimension from the lowest extremity to the highest extremity.

name: width
definition: The measurement of the extent of something from side to side. Width is the measurement from left to right.

name: colourDescription
definition: A description of a colour of an object.

name: identificationSchemeName
definition: The name of the identification scheme.

name: identificationSchemeAgencyName
definition: The name of the agency that maintains the identification scheme.

name: identificationSchemeAgencyCode
definition: The identification of the agency that maintains the identification scheme.

definition: Number specifying a line in the referenced document.

definition: <font color="#1b1b1b">The type of additional identification for a logistic unit. </font>

name: beginTime
definition: Time specifying the start time for the date time range.

name: endDate
definition: Date specifying the last day for the date time range.

name: endTime
definition: Time specifying the end time for the date time range.

name: timeMeasurementUnitCode
definition: Any standardized, reproducible unit that can be used to measure any physical property.

name: timePeriodDue
definition: Measurement specifying the duration of the period within which the payment in due, for example within 10 days.

name: gpcAttributeValueName
definition: The GS1 provided text equivalent of the Global Product Classification Attribute Value Code.

name: gpcAttributeValueCode
definition: The GS1 provided code which identifies the Global Product Classification Attribute Value.

name: colourCode
definition: A code depicting the colour of an object according to a specified code list.

name: additionalTradeItemClassificationCodeListCode
definition: Code specifying the applied additional trade item classification scheme. Allowed values are specified in GS1 code list AdditionalTradeItemClassificationCodeListCode.

name: codeListVersion
definition: The version of the applied additional trade item classification scheme.

definition: Category code based on alternate classification schema chosen in addition to the Global Product Classification (GPC).

name: additionalReturnableAssetIdentificationTypeCode

name: additionalConsignmentIdentification

name: additionalLogisiticUnitIdentification
definition: Additional (non-SSCC) identification attached to a shipping container or shipping package and used for logistical and traceability purposes.

name: additionalShipmentIdentification
definition: Additional identification key used to identify a shipment.

name: additionalTradeItemIdentification
definition: Alternative means to the Global Trade Item Number to identify a trade item.

name: additionalPartyIdentification
definition: Identifier of the party or location, specified in addition to the GLN.

name: additionalServiceRelationIdentification
definition: The additional key used to identify the relationship between a service provider and service recipient

name: additionalIndividualAssetIdentification
definition: Identifier of the asset, specified in addition to the GIAI.

name: additionalReturnableAssetIdentification
definition: The additional identification Key used to identify returnable assets.

name: gsrn
definition: Global Service Relation Number(GSRN), the GS1 key used for the identification of relationships between service providers and service recipients.

name: grai
definition: Global Returnable Asset Identifier (GRAI), the GS1 key used for the identification of returnable assets.

name: giai
definition: Global Individual Asset Identifier (GIAI), the GS1 key used for the identification of individual assets.

name: isExemptFromPremarketAuthorisation
definition: Indicates whether the medical device is exempt from premarket regulations.  For the FDA, Premarket approval (PMA) is the process of scientific and regulatory review to evaluate the safety and effectiveness of Class III medical devices. Class III devices are those that support or sustain human life, are of substantial importance in preventing impairment of human health, or which present a potential, unreasonable risk of illness or injury. Due to the level of risk associated with Class III devices, FDA has determined that general and special controls alone are insufficient to assure the safety and effectiveness of class III devices. Therefore, these devices require a premarket approval (PMA) application under section 515 of the FD&C Act in order to obtain marketing clearance. Please note that some Class III preamendment devices may require a Class III 510(k).

definition: The unique identification (ID) that provides a trade item's certification standard value, official licensing number or identification which proves that a product/process has passed the certification procedure.

name: recallPrecision
definition: The precision of the Recall or Field Safety Corrective Action (FSCA). Information about the Recall of FCSA should include the details of the recalled elements (batch numbers, lots numbers , etc.) of the Device. This information is applicable when the scope of a recall is entered manually by the user (not by referencing an Field Safety Notifice (FSN))

name: illustrationTypeCode
definition: Identifies the type of illustration or other content to which an occurrence of the composite refers. Mandatory in each occurrence

name: packagingMaterialColourCodeReference
definition: Identifies the packaging material colour.

name: physiochemicalCharacteristicWarningValueBasis
definition: Used to express the analytical circumstances in which the warning value was measured (e.g. in 10 g or 200 mg/kg). This is to specify the circumstance of the metric a foundation of the measure values has to be.

name: quantityOfBatteriesRequired
definition: The number of batteries required to operate the trade item.

name: minimumOrderValue
definition: The minimum order value of the trade item expressed in a money amount that can be ordered. This attribute is to be used with a respective currency (e.g. 1000.00 USD).

name: freezingMeltingPoint
definition: The temperature at which its crystals are in equilibrium with the liquid phase at atmospheric pressure.

name: additionalPublicationDescription
definition: The publication description to be used for marketing purposes (i.e. cover description, review).

name: avpList
definition: Attribute value pair information.

name: storageRequirementsDescription
definition: A description how to safely store the Trade Item for example cool, dry, not near flame, adequate ventilation.

name: lightBulbShapeCode
definition: Light bulbs come in a range of shapes and sizes. The names of the shapes vary somewhat from region to region. Many of these shapes have a designation consisting of one or more letters followed by one or more numbers, e.g. A55 or PAR38. The letters represent the shape of the bulb. The numbers represent the maximum diameter, either in 1/8 of an inch, or in millimetres, depending on the shape and the region. For example, 63 mm reflectors are designated R63, but in the US, they are known as R20 (2.5 in).  However, in both regions, a PAR38 reflector is known as PAR38. Additional details on light bulb shapes can be found at sites such as http://www.eaglelight.com/category/lighting_tutorials.bulb_shapes/.

name: targetMarketConsumerSalesConditionCode
definition: A code depicting restrictions imposed on the Trade Item regarding how it can be sold to the consumer for example age restrictions, selling restrictions.

name: netDueTimePeriod
definition: Time period amount should be paid. For example: 30 DAY.

name: packagingRenewableContentRatio
definition: The ratio of renewable material used to total material used in packaging constituents, components, units of packaging or packaging systems.

name: meshMaterialCode
definition: The material used to create the mesh strainer in the product. The mesh provides particulate filtration for the unit.

name: directPartMarkingIdentifier
definition: A number or marking placed directly on the medical device for example DLC-2200.

name: extremelyHazardousSubstanceQuantity
definition:
The quantity of substance that is considered to be extremely hazardous under a regulatory threshold. 
For SARA, this is the threshold planning quantity in pounds per 40 Code of Federal Regulations (CFR) under section 302 of SARA Title 3.

name: subjectSchemeVersion
definition: A number which identifies a version or edition of the subject scheme specified in the associated element.

name: includedOperatingSystem
definition: The operating system loaded on the trade item, device or upon which the software is designed to operate.

name: udidFirstPublicationDateTime
definition: The date upon which a Unique Device Identification Database (UDID) can publish the Trade Item Information into their public facing systems.  The value can be different for each UDID GLN based on when it should be published by each UDID. Each UDID needs a single non-changeable date upon which to derive when to publish information to their public facing systems.

name: dangerousGoodsLimitedQuantitiesCode
definition: A code defined by by an agency specifying whether a dangerous good can be packaged in small quantities providing they are packaged and labelled in accordance with certain requirements. Note: for 3.1.8, this attribute replaces aDRDangerousGoodsLimitedQuantityCode.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: organicCertificationIdentification
definition: A reference issued to confirm that something has passed organic certification.

name: productCharacteristicValueInteger
definition: The product characteristic value expressed as an integer.

name: transportationModeCode
definition: The type of vehicle used for the transportation of a hazardous material.

name: dutyFeeTaxClassificationCode
definition: A code specifying the broad category of duty, fee or tax for example energy. waste, environment.

name: totalPackagingEconomicCostMeasurementCode
definition: A code determining the packaging component, material, etc that is cost and being determined for.

name: sequenceNumber
definition: A number which specifies a single overall sequence of contributor names

name: preparationConsumptionPrecautions
definition: Specifies additional precautions to be taken before preparation or consumption of the product.

name: apparelDetailTypeCode
definition: The type of detail on a the apparel product.

name: colourFamilyCode
definition: Indicates the family code of the product colour.

name: batteryWattHourRating
definition: The watt rating for the specified battery material qualifier as specified by the manufacturer of the item.

name: isTradeItemReinstated
definition: Indicator stating the Trade Item is being reinstated and will no longer be cancelled or discontinued. The canceledDate or discontinuedDate has been altered to reflect the reinstatement.

name: languageCode
definition: A code representing the language used in the description.

name: extentUnitCode
definition: An ONIX code indicating the unit used for the <ExtentValue> and the format in which the value is presented. Mandatory in each occurrence of the <Extent> composite, and non-repeating.

name: feedingAmountBasisDescription
definition: The basis code to qualify the feeding amounts being specified.  For example 1 per day.

name: productCharacteristicCode
definition: The name of the product characteristic being described for example numberOfPlys.

name: isLightBulbSuitableForAccentLighting
definition: Indicates the light bulb is suitable for accent lighting. For directional lamps only, and if the angle of the light beam of the lamp = 90 ° and its useful luminous flux must be measured in a cone of 120°.

name: productTextureAgencyCode
definition: The code for the agency which maintains the food and drinks texture or thickness code list. For example, International Dysphagia Diet Standardisation Initiative (IDSSI)

name: dutyFeeTaxCountryCode
definition: The country that a duty, fee or tax may be applicable to for a trade item.

name: precautionaryStatementsDescription
definition: A description of the measures listed on a hazardous label to minimize or prevent adverse effects.

name: studioName
definition: The name of the company (called studio in the film industry) that made the publication

name: udidDeviceCount
definition: The count of medical devices which are contained inside the base item for regulatory purposes."  This information is part of the UDID regulatory requirements and would be populated at the lowest level of a hierarchy.  Device count is not the same as net content as a single device can contain multiple uses.

name: audioVisualMediaProductTitle
definition: Title of the audio visual media product.

name: applicationIdentifierTypeCode
definition: Indication of which Application Identifier's (AI) presence is indicated for example 10 (batch number),15 (best-before-date),17 (expiry date), 310(n) (net weight in kilogram).

name: languageCode
definition: A code representing the language used in the description.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: feedCompositionStatement
definition: List of the animal feed composition data, based on the ingredients contained in the feed, as governed by local rules and regulations.

name: gHSSymbolDescriptionCode
definition:
A code depicting the symbols which convey health, physical and environmental hazard information, assigned to a hazard class and category for example GHS. 
Pictograms include the harmonized hazard symbols plus other graphic elements, such as borders, background patterns or colours that are intended to convey specific information. 
Examples of all the pictograms and downloadable files for GHS can be accessed on the UN website for the GHS.

name: regulatedChemicalName
definition: The name of a chemical regulated by a chemical regulation or agency. For example Chlorobenzene.

name: subTitle
definition: The text of a subtitle, if any. ‘Subtitle‘ means any added words which appear with the title element given in an occurrence of the <TitleElement> composite, and which amplify and explain the title element, but which are not considered to be part of the title element itself.

name: gln
definition: Global Location Number (GLN), the GS1 key used for the identification of parties and locations.

name: ingredientStatement
definition:
Information on the constituent ingredient make up of the product specified as one string. 

This attribute will be migrated to the nonfoodIngredientStatement in the future

name: areBatteriesBuiltIn
definition: This code is defined as an indicator whether or not any batteries included with the trade item are built into the trade item during manufacturing. and cannot be changed or removed.

name: labelledTemperature
definition: The temperature(s) that is/are labelled on the trade item to help the consumer understand the temperatures for which the product can be used, e.g. the washing temperature(s) for a detergent.

name: designer
definition: The person or company that designed the product. This may or may not be the brand name. For example, Guess Jeans designers were Paul and Maurice Marciano.

name: namesBeforeKey
definition: Part of a structured name of a person who contributed to the creation of the product: name(s) and/or initial(s) preceding a person’s key name(s), e.g. James J

name: informationProvider
definition: The Global Location Number of the originator of the data. This could either be a data source or a data recipient.

name: garmentAdornmentTypeCode
definition: A code indicating the form of an adornment or embellishment to an item.

name: ingredientContentPercentageMeasurementPrecisionCode
definition: The measurement precision qualifying the ingredient content percentage for example LESS_THAN.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: massEquivalentProtocolDescription
definition: The protocol description related to the mass equivalent code.

name: additiveStatement
definition: Statement on presence or absence of additives or genetic modification contained in the trade item for example "Contains no preservatives, no artificial colours or flavours and no artificial flavours".

name: tradeItemLicenseStartDateTime
definition: The effective start date of the license to use the title, character or any trademarked assets that are used on the trade item.

name: areBatteriesRequired
definition: Indicates if batteries are required to operate the trade item.

name: importClassificationValue
definition: The value for an associated import classification type.

name: feedLifestage
definition: Identifies the life-stage of the animal for which a trade item has been designed for example Adult.

name: aquaticEutrophicationModelCode
definition: The model determining the degree of aquatic eutrophication

name: alcoholBeverageFilteringMethodTypeCode
definition: The method by which an alcohol beverage product has been filtered. Filtering is used to refine or polish the product to achieve a specific taste profile. Example: Charcoal, Chilled.

name: totalPackagingEconomicCostAmountBasis
definition: The basis amount or quantity used to determine the packaging costs for example 1 kg, 1000 units, 1 year

name: lowerExplosiveLimit
definition: The low end value expressed as a percent by volume that the mixture is still flammable.

name: discountDescription
definition: A text field describing the discount.

name: cumulativeEnergyDemandProtocolDescription
definition: The reference protocol description used to represent the potential to cumulative energy demand.

name: isTradeItemADespatchUnit
definition: An indicator identifying that the information provider considers the trade item as a despatch (shipping) unit. This may be relationship dependent based on channel of trade or other point to point agreement.

name: uDIProductionIdentifierTypeCode
definition: The Production Identifiers which are used to control the product as relevant for Unique Device Identification (UDI) rules. Example: Expiry Date, Manufacturing Date, Serial Number, Lot (or batch) Number, etc.

name: dosageRecommendation
definition: Information pertaining to the dosage of drug or supplement that should be taken/administered per dose. This is not based upon prescribed dosage, but recommended dosage. This may be pre-labelled on product or need to be labelled per target market regulations. Example Take 2 tablets every 4 hours, Take 1 teaspoon daily, etc.

name: isPrimaryMaterial
definition: Specifies whether the primary or majority material in a composite material used for packaging.

name: garmentLengthTypeCode
definition: A code indicating the length of a garment where the hem line falls on mid or lower body.

name: dataCarrierTypeCode
definition: A code indicating the type of data carrier physically present on the trade item.

name: postProcessTradeItemTreatmentPhysicalCode
definition: Produce has gone some physical process whether altered or other physical processes after harvesting.

name: usageDuringBreastFeedingCode
definition: Indicates if the trade item can be used or not during breast feeding.

name: doesTradeItemMeetWholeGrainRichCriteria
definition: An indication the trade item meets the whole grain-rich criteria as defined and regulated by the applicable Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body.

name: exceptionMessageTypeCode
definition: The type of GS1 exception message being received for example GDSN.

name: supplierSpecifiedMinimumConsumerStorageDays
definition: Represents the number of days between a product's "sell by date" and its "use by date".

name: packagingCompositeMaterialDescription
definition: A description ofany composite material used in packaging. A composite material is a combination of different material. types, e.g. Paper-Cardboard / Plastic / Aluminium, or Composite majority Plastics.

name: priceComparisonContentTypeCode
definition: Code indicating how the value in Price Comparison Measurement is used to calculate the comparative price, which is printed on shelf labels.

name: additionalTradeItemClassificationCodeDescription
definition: Description of the additional classification bundle (code/agency + description).

name: imitationOrSubstituteFor
definition: The name of the imitated or substitute product. Example: The GTIN product name is Ketchup type sauce, this value would be Ketchup.

name: streetNumber
definition: The street number portion of the street address for the contact.

name: contactName
definition: The name of the company or person associated with the contact type. For example, in case of a contact type of CONSUMER_SUPPORT, this could be the company name as expressed on the trade item packaging or label.

name: lastUpdateParty
definition: The Global Location Number of the data pool responsible for modifying / updating the party record in the GS1 GR.

name: nominalOutsideDiameter
definition: The measurement of the nominal (not the exact measurement) outside diameter of the plumbing connection point of the trade item.

name: audioVisualMediaProductLabelName
definition: The name of the company (called label in the music industry) that made the music publication.

name: opacityTypeCode
definition: A code to describe the opacity achieved by the product. The codes may vary by product type. Examples Cosmetics, Glass, Paints and Wood Stains.

name: regulationTypeCode
definition: A code that indicates that a trade item is in compliance with specific applicable government regulations.

name: packagingDepth
definition: The depth of the packaging, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard. If the packaging dimensions are for a platform or pallet, the measurements for the platform or pallet itself are provided based on the orientation and tolerances for non-consumer trade items.

name: consumerProductVariantReasonCode
definition: A code describing the impacted change (packaging change, graphics change, minor formulation, etc) for a Consumer Product Variant.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: creditableGrainStandard
definition: The standard gram value applicable to the creditable grain gram group code.

name: returnablePackageDepositIdentification
definition: In some markets the deposit information is specified by a GTIN giving the type of returnable package on which a deposit is charged. Each deposit code is associated with an amount specified elsewhere. The enumeration list is maintained externally.

name: physiochemicalCharacteristicReferenceValueBasis
definition: Used to express the analytical circumstances in which the reference value was measured (e.g. in 10 g or 200 mg/kg). This is to specify the circumstance of the metric a foundation of the measure values has to be.

name: bendAngleCode
definition: The type of bend or angle for the product. For example a pipe made to turn a corner might have a bend angle of 90 degrees.

name: toxicologicalInformationDescription
definition: A general description of any information on any toxic properties as included on the MSDS for example precautionary text on a label. This text should describe the key issues with the product in regards to toxicity.

name: numberOfServingsPerPackageMeasurementPrecisionCode
definition: The total number of servings contained in the package.

name: relationshipEffectiveEndDateTime
definition: The day on which the price synchronization relationship ends.

name: displayTypeCode
definition: A code determining the type of display a trade item is, for example Shelf Display Ready Packaging.

name: physicalResourceTypeCode
definition: A code depicting the type of physical resource being measured for usage for example electricity, gas.

name: sizeCodeListCode
definition: Code specifying a size code list. Allowed code values are specified in GS1 Code List SizeCodeListCode.

name: totalCreditableIngredientTypeAmount
definition: The sum total creditable amount of all the creditable ingredient type(s) applicable for the item as calculated using the requirements, rules and regulations set forth by the applicable Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body.  Per US regulations total creditable amount must be rounded down to the nearest quarter (0.25) ounce equivalent in the US target market.

name: drainedWeight
definition: The weight of the trade item when drained of its liquid. For example 225 "grm", Jar of pickles in vinegar. Applies to defined bricks of GCI Global trade item Classification - Mainly food trade item. Has to be associated with a valid UoM.

name: consumerSalesConditionMaximumAmount
definition: The maximum amount of the trade item that can be sold to the consumer at POS (Point Of Sale). This amount may be regulated by law in some markets.

name: width
definition: The width of the trade item, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard. If the trade item is a unit load, include the shipping platform unless it is excluded according to the platformTypeCode chosen.

name: isPackagingMaterialRecoverable
definition: Determines whether packaging material is recoverable. Recoverable materials are those which are capable of being reused or returned to use in the form of raw materials

name: cancelDateTime
definition: Date assigned by data source and stored in the source data pool reflecting the date the catalogue item was cancelled. This date will also be stored in the Registry.

name: chemicalIngredientName
definition: The common name of the chemical ingredient.

name: microbiologicalOrganismMinimumValue
definition: The minimum allowable value of the microbiological organism per weight or volume in a specific environment.

name: suffixToKey
definition: Part of a structured name of a person who contributed to the creation of the product: a suffix following a person’s key name(s), e.g. ‘Jr’ or ‘III’.

name: footwearOutsoleTypeCode
definition: A code indicating the type of outsole of the footwear.

name: specialDeviceTypeCode
definition: The type of special medical device the product is. Example: Orthopaedic, Rigid Gas Permeable (RGP) & Made-to-Order Soft Contact Lenses, Software

name: productCharacteristicValueDescription
definition: The product characteristic value expressed as a description (text with language.

name: packagingRawMaterialContentPercentage
definition: <font color="#002c6c">The percentage of the type of raw or recycled material the product packaging material is made from, as specified by the Packaging Raw Material Code.</font>

name: exposureMode
definition: Description of each of the various automatic or manual exposure (shooting) modes a camera comes with for example, P (programmed auto), S (shutter-priority auto), A (aperture-priority auto), M (manual).

name: countrySubdivisionCode
definition: The country subdivision in which a processing or other activity has been performed for example processing, bottling, manufacturing.

name: organicPercentClaim
definition: The percent of actual organic materials per weight of the trade item. This is usually claimed on the product.

name: clinicallyRelevantCharacteristicOfMedicalDevice
definition: Terms used to describe the clinical characteristics which are relevant for the trade item.  These terms will refer to measurement or size appropriate for the trade item, for example 8F Catheter.

name: acidificationMeasurementReferenceSubstanceCode
definition: The reference substance used to represent the potential to acidify ecosystems.

name: quantityOfBatteriesBuiltIn
definition: The quantity of batteries built into the trade item during manufacturing. This includes batteries that can or cannot be changed or removed.

name: packagingMaterialTypeCode
definition: A code that provides the packaging material.

name: acidificationMeasurementProtocolDescription
definition: The reference protocol description used to represent the potential to acidify ecosystems.

name: gpcAttributeTypeDefinition
definition: The GS1 provided definition of the Global Product Classification Attribute Code.

name: doesTradeItemHaveAutoReaderTracker
definition: Indication that the trade item has a device that identifies that the product has a limited number of reuses and is self tracked. Each time the device is used / plugged in it will decrement the count. When the counter reaches zero the trade item should be disposed of.

name: yearOfAnnual
definition: When the year of an annual is part of a title, this field should be used to carry the year (or, if required, a spread of years such as 2009-2010). Optional and non-repeating.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: codeListVersion
definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

name: audienceCodeValueCode
definition: Identifies the applicable values of the appropriate audienceCodeType.  For Audience Code Type 01 (Onix Type) this value should be populated with Onix Audience Code 28 (Books: Onix Audience Code Value Code)

name: zoomTypeCode
definition: A code depicting the type of zoom the device or lens has for example DIGITAL or OPTICAL.

name: packagingRawMaterialCode
definition: <font color="#002c6c">The code describing the type of raw or recycled material the product packaging material is made from. </font>

name: isBulkUpdate
definition: Indicates that the update to the condition is for a full price list update. This update may include price increase, price decrease, unchanged prices or new prices. This price change is managed globally by the retailer

name: audienceTypeCodeListCode
definition: Identifies the broad audience or readership for which a product is intended. Repeatable if the product is intended for two or more groups.

name: seamsCode
definition: A code indicating the characteristic of the seams of a product.

name: consumerFirstAvailabilityDateTime
definition: The first date/time that the buyer is allowed to sell the trade item to consumers. Usually related to a specific geography. ISO 8601 date format CCYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.

name: languageCode
definition: A code representing the language used in the description.

name: accidentalReleaseMeasuresDescription
definition: A description of the method of clean-up or pick up for example Chemtrack number in relation to any hazardous materials regulated by ADR (European Agreement concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road).

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: alcoholicBeverageSubregion
definition: A legally defined geographical region where the grapes for a wine were grown also know as an appellation.

name: propertyFloat
definition: A property of  a classification of an item expressed as a float for example 0.00.

name: errorDescription
definition: A message that is returned by the GDSN, if an error occurs during the handling of a command.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: isTradeItemExemptFromSerialisation
definition: Indicator that a trade item is exempt from current serialisation requirements, for example US requirements. Serialization and traceability requirements may vary by product and country.  In some existing instances, certain products have been granted an exception to these regulatory requirements. This attribute will indicate to supply chain participants (wholesalers and dispensers) clearly if a product is expected to be in compliance with serialisation and traceability requirements in their country.

name: packagingOwnerIdentification
definition: The GLN of the owner of the packaging.

name: productUsageBodyLocationCode
definition: Indicates the body location for which the product is intended to be used for example HAND.

name: hosierySockRiseCode
definition: A code indicating how high hosiery and socks rise on the wearer's leg.

name: sourceAnimalCode
definition: The source of raw material used to produce the food product for example a goat for milk.

name: productTextureCode
definition: Specify the texture or thickness of the contained product as a code.

name: sparePartsAvailabilityEffectiveDateTypeCode
definition: The type of date expressed as a code associated with the period of availability of spare parts usually expressed as an event date for the item for example DATE_OF_PURCHASE_BY_CONSUMER, DATE_OF_MANUFACTURE or DATE_OF_DELIVERY.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: isDutyFeeTaxTypeIncludedInPrice
definition: The indicator that specifies whether the type of duty, tax or fee applicable to the trade item, is included in the price. This will vary according to the target market or buyer.

name: childNutritionValue
definition: Actual value for the child nutrition qualifier as specified in the child nutrition statement or label.  For example. if a 4.5 ounce serving provides 1/8 cup red-orange vegetable, the childNutritionValue is 1/8 cup.

name: fileDepictedSeason
definition: A description of the season shown or depicted within the digital asset. (e.g. Winter, Spring).

name: alcoholicBeverageColourCode
definition: Indicates the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the colour of the alcoholic beverage. Alcohol colours are sometimes qualified by a a scale or regulation. Examples: Wine Regulations, Beer – EBC, SRM/Lovibond, etc.

name: hazardousWasteDescription
definition: A description of the classification of hazardous waste managed at the federal or state level for example EPA Hazardous Waste Code of D001 ( Ignitable waste).

name: firstReturnableDateTime
definition: The first date on or after which non-sold trade items can be returned. This information provides the retailer with any conditions required by the information provider as to the date on or after which non-sold trade items may be returned in order to receive credit from the appropriate party.

name: paymentTermsTypeCode
definition: The type of  payment term expressed as a code, for example DISCOUNT.

name: sourceCertificationSystemProtocolDescription
definition: Provides the organisation(s) identification that certifies the source. (e.g. Forest Stewardship Council, Sustainable Forestry Initiative, Programme for Endorsement of Forest Certification.)

name: tradeItemIntroductionYear
definition: The date the GTIN and/or trade item is introduced into the marketplace. Once established this does not change.

name: targetConsumerUsageTypeCode
definition: A code identifying the type of usage criteria for the target consumer that will use the product for example AGE, HEIGHT.

name: variableWeightAllowableDeviationPercentage
definition: Indication of the percentage value that the actual weight of the trade item may differ from the average or estimated weight given. For example, Roast beef off the bone 3.5 kg, Gross weight 3500 Grams, Range = 14 %. This means that this item may be produced with weight values ranging from 3.010 kg to 3.990 kg.

name: licenseCode
definition: A code indicating the insignia of the league/sport/event which a given item bears.

name: nutritionalLabelTypeCode
definition: Code indicating that the trade item is eligible for certain nutritional labelling programs according to a specific regulation

name: globalWarmingPotentialEquivalent
definition: The associated mass of CO<sub>2 </sub>equivalents associated with the Functional Unit.

name: organicTradeItemCode
definition: Used to indicate the organic status of a trade item or of one or more of its components.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: packagingWidth
definition: The width of the packaging, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard. If the packaging dimensions are for a platform or pallet, the measurements for the platform or pallet itself are provided based on the orientation and tolerances for non-consumer trade items.

name: servingSizeDescription
definition: A free text field specifying the serving size for which the nutrient information has been stated for example: per 1/3 cup (42 g).

name: exactPH
definition: The exact PH amount for a chemical ingredient (not a range).

name: targetConsumerAgeGroup
definition: A description of a general age group the product is designed for. This would not include the actual age ranges. For example Infant, Toddler, Child, Teen, Adult.

name: totalVegetableSubgroupAmount
definition: The creditable amount of the vegetable subgroup in the item.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: tablewareTypeCode
definition: A code indicating the type of a tabletop products.

name: lastShipDateTime
definition: Indicates the latest date that the trade item can be shipped. This is independent of any specific ship-from location.

name: isDistributionMethodPrimary
definition: Indicates if the delivery method for the trade item is the primary one.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: dutyFeeTaxEffectiveStartDateTime
definition: The effective date on which the tax, fee or duty must start being collected.

name: extension
definition: An extension point for a Price Condition.

name: targetedConsumptionBy
definition: The type of animal this food is intended to be consumed by.

name: apparelDetailSizeCode
definition: The size of the detail application/logo.

name: referencedTradeItemTypeCode
definition: A code depicting the type of trade item that is referenced for a specific purpose for example substitute, replaced by, equivalent trade items.

name: communityVisibilityDateTime
definition: The date from which the neutral trade item information (i.e. not the private information, not relationship-dependent data and not price data) is available to all members of the target data pool, without restriction.  Until this date only the data recipients to whom the data source has explicitly published the data can have access to the data.  By setting this date a data source gives permission for wider publication of the generic item data.

name: minimumTemperature
definition: The minimum temperature that a trade item can be held below defined by the manufacturer without affecting product safety or quality.

name: transactionalMeasurementUnitCode
definition: A measurement unit code including codes in addition to UN Rec 20 codes used in business transactions including UN Rec 21 codes for pallets, cases, etc.

name: isChemicalRegulationCompliant
definition: Determines whether or not a chemical is compliant with a specific regulation (driven by chemicalRegulationName).

definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: physicalFormDescription
definition: A description of the form of the product for example gas, liquid, powder.  Colorless, Fragrant, Liquid in relation to any hazardous materials.

name: countryCode
definition: Code specifying the country for the address.

name: hasDeviceMeasuringFunction
definition: Indication if the device has a function which measures any type of patient metrics.

name: stackingPatternTypeCode
definition: Indicates the pattern the product is stacked on a logistics unit, for example column pattern or interlocking pattern.

name: pipeScheduleIdentification
definition: The pipe schedule or rating size as defined by an external agency for example Schedule 40 or SDR-9. A pipe schedule is how this is classified in regards to the functions of the pipe including type of medium (e.g. solid, liquid or gas) and pressure rating.

name: collectionIdentifier
definition: Identifier of the type specified in the collectionIDType field.

name: lastUpdateDateTime
definition: The date and time when the party record is modified/ updated.

name: sDSStandardVersion
definition: The version of the standard used to create the MSDS that is pointed to in the SDS URL.

name: systemOrProcedurePackMedicalPurposeDescription
definition: Descriptive terms to denote the Medical Purpose of the System or Procedure Pack. Applicable for System and Procedure Packs and refers to the indication of the specific medical purpose of the System or Procedure Pack.

name: foodBeverageCompositionDatabaseCode
definition: A code depicting and agency which manages a food composition database that applies to regulatory nutrition information for example the Government of Canada.

name: packagingMaterialCoatingTypeDescription
definition: Specifies any coating material that is applied to the packaging material.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: numberOfCyclesPriorToWithdrawal
definition: Determines   reusability in accordance with EN 13429 or ISO/DIS18603.

name: packagingMaterialCompositionQuantity
definition: The quantity of the packaging material of the trade item. Can be weight, volume or surface, can vary by country.

name: departmentName
definition: The name of the department that can be contacted to provide additional information

name: garmentLegTypeCode
definition: A code indicating the form or fit of the leg portion of a pair of pants or jeans.

name: displayScreenBezelSize
definition: The measurement from the edge of physical screen to the frame.

name: skinProductFunctionOrTreatmentCode
definition: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify different functions of the skin care or moisturizing product and other treatments.

name: targetSurfaceTypeCode
definition: The surfaces a product is intended to be used upon. Some manufacturers designate one or more specific surface types from this list to help consumers understand product application.

name: handlingInstructionsDescription
definition: Information and processes needed to safely handle the trade item. Intended to be sent when handling Instructions Code and agency have not been provided.

name: sequenceNumber
definition: A number used to indicate the order in which the allowances or charges are to be calculated.

name: isReloadReasonCode
definition: A code depicting the reason for requesting a reload.

name: acceleration
definition: The rate of change of velocity. For example: 0 - 60 mph / 4.3 s; 0 - 100 kph / 4.5 s.

name: consumerPackageDisclaimer
definition: Additional information that should be used in advertising and in displaying.

name: avpList
definition: <font color="#ff0000">Attribute value pair information.</font>

name: lastChangeDateTime
definition: Indicates the point in time where the last modification on a Trade Item was made.

name: upperExplosiveLimit
definition: The high end value expressed as a percent by volume that the product will still explode.

name: eRGNumber
definition:
A number used to find the correct section within the Emergency Response Guide.  The ERG is a guide to first responders to quickly identify the material involved in an incident for example a fire or spill.  It is derivative from the UN Number.
Note: The ERG number is only required in the United States.

name: packagingMarkedNutritionLabelCode
definition: Indication of which nutrition call outs or highlights are on the package. A nutrition call out is a graphic which highlights some elements from the nutrition panel for the consumer to have a quick view for example, Front of Package information.

name: editionVersionNumber
definition: The number of a numbered revision within an edition number. To be used only where a publisher uses such two-level numbering to indicate revisions which do not constitute a new edition under a new ISBN or other distinctive product identifier. Optional and non-repeating. If this field is used, an <EditionNumber> must also be present.

name: financialAccountName
definition: Text specifying the name of the financial account.

name: priceValue
definition: Associates a percent or integer value with a price value.

name: physicalResourceUsageRatingScaleCodeReference
definition: The value in a range or scale of efficiency of the product is rated, for example, spectrum  A – G.

name: registrationDateTime
definition: The date and time when the party record is initiated / created in the GS1 Global Registry.

name: sender
definition: Identifies the party sending an electronic message by use of the Global Location Number-- The globally unique EAN.UCC System identification number for physical, functional, or legal entities. The Global Location Number uses the EAN/UCC-13 Data Structure.

name: contactTypeCode
definition: Code specifying the function or role of a contact.

name: extension
definition: Extension point for inclusion of additional information through an extension to the document.

name: physicalResourceUsageMeasurementBasis
definition: The basis used to determine the resource usage for the trade item for example time period (e.g. hours, days, years).

name: partyStartEffectiveDateTime
definition: The date and time that the party becomes active.

name: minimumValue
definition: Specifies the lower limit of the string range.

name: proofOfPackagingWeightReductionStandardCode
definition: The standard for the proof of packaging weight reduction is based on.

name: receiver
definition: Identifies the party receiving an electronic message by use of the Global Location Number-- The globally unique EAN.UCC System identification number for physical, functional, or legal entities. The Global Location Number uses the EAN/UCC-13 Data Structure.

name: animalNutrientQuantityContained
definition: Measurement value indicating the amount of the nutrient contained in the animal food or nutrition product. It is expressed relative to the animal nutrient quantity contained basis measurement.  For example, 3 grams in the case of 3 grams per 12 kilogram.  Allows for the representation of the same value in different units of measure but not multiple values.

name: tradeItemUnitDescriptorCode
definition: Describes the hierarchical level of the trade item. The attribute tradeItemUnitDescriptorCode is mandatory. Examples: "CASE", ”PALLET”.

name: isHomogenised
definition: The indication whether or not the milk used was actively homogenised. The homogenisation of milk is a technical process in the dairy. The milk fat is milled to such an extent that further creaming is prevented.

name: additionalTradeItemClassificationSystemCode
definition: The Classification System for the Additional Trade Item Classification.

name: dangerousGoodsTransportCategoryCode
definition: Trade items classified as dangerous goods are divided into transport categories for the purpose of calculating what quantity of dangerous goods is allowed to be transported on the same transport unit under specific exemption rules.

name: maximumTemperature
definition: The maximum temperature that a trade item can not exceed as defined by the manufacturer without affecting product safety or quality.

name: contextIdentification
definition: An identification for a context.

name: isSubstanceOfVeryHighConcern
definition:
An indicator that a trade item contains substances of very high concern (SVHC) according to REACH as defined in as defined in Article 57 of Regulation (EC) No 1907/2006. This indication does not mean the contained substance or substances have been added to the REACH Candidate List. Substances of very high concern (SVHC) are defined as:
•Substances that are category 1 and 2 carcinogens, mutagens or toxic to the reproductive system (CMR) 
•Substances that are persistent, bio-accumulative and toxic (PBT) or very persistent and very bio-accumulative (vPvB) 
•Substances such as endocrine disrupters, which are demonstrated to be of equivalent concern. For these substances, there are specific requirements under the REACH Regulation.

name: bracketTierMaximum
definition: The upper limits for qualification for a bracket.

name: deauthorisationDateTime
definition: Last date on which the item will be authorised for sale to a location.

name: propertyAmount
definition: A property of  a classification of an item expressed as an amount (value and currency).

name: importClassificationCountrySubdivisionRegionOfOrigin
definition: The region of origin of the trade item for import purposes. This is required by Intrastat.

name: contactAddress
definition: The address associated with the contact type. For example, in case of a contact type of CONSUMER_SUPPORT, this could be the full company address as expressed on the trade item packaging or label.

name: contactDescription
definition: A description of the contact for the trade item.

name: servingSize
definition: Measurement value specifying the serving size or portion. In some markets, due to regulation, this information is used as the basis amount that a nutrient is measured against. Example: Per 30 grams. 1/2 cup, etc. Please refer to the target markets implementation guideline on how to populate this attribute.

name: tradeItemConditionCode
definition: The code depicting the type of preparation that a trade item may require before being sold to the consumer (e.g. cut for sale, portioned/pieced). This preparation should be done by the buyer.

name: contextEffectiveEndDateTime
definition: The date at which a the registration of a context is no longer effective.

name: recommendedConsumerPickupAreaCode
definition: The recommended placement for the consumer purchase decision point of the item and location within the retail store . For example a potato salad bulk my need to be portioned to a consumer at a service counter as the purchase amount is dependent on what the consumer would like to purchase.

name: awardPrizeDescription
definition: A text that describes the awards a film won.

name: individualUnitMaximumSize
definition: Maximum size of the individual unit inside the lowest level of packaging.

name: preliminaryItemStatusCode
definition: A code designating whether the trade item has data that the information provider intends to correct or add values to due to pre-production unknowns (PRELIMINARY) or whether the item has attribute values that reflect go to market state (FINAL).

name: catalogueItemStateCode
definition: The four states are: Registered , Cancelled, In Progress and Discontinued .

name: responseStatus
definition: The response status for a Party Registration, expressed as a code for example Accepted

name: conditionValue
definition: Provides a value or percent associated with a condition

name: streetAddressThree
definition: The third free form line of an address. This third part is printed on paper as the third line below the name. The third free form line complements the first and second free form lines where necessary.

name: dailyValueIntakeReference
definition: Free text field specifying the daily value intake base for on which the daily value intake per nutrient has been based. Example: “Based on a 2000 calorie diet.”

name: codeListVersion
definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

name: height
definition: The height of the trade item, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard. If the trade item is a unit load, include the shipping platform unless it is excluded according to the platformTypeCode chosen.

name: referencedTradeItemTypeCode
definition: A code depicting the type of trade item that is referenced for a specific purpose for example substitute, replaced by, equivalent trade items.

name: certificationAssessmentDateTime
definition: The date and time that an assessment was performed on a Trade Item that led to a certification.

name: gpcCategoryCode
definition: Code specifying a product category according to the GS1 Global Product Classification (GPC) standard.

name: speciesForFisheryStatisticsPurposesName
definition: The scientific name associated with the speciesforFisheryStatisticsPurposesCode.

definition: Number to be used for identification and referencing of subsequent updates to a business document.

name: transportationMaximumQuantity
definition: The maximum inner volume of receptacles or packages (inner pack of vendor pack) that can be safely transported for a specific transportation type (e.g. Air Cargo) according to a governing agency.

name: shippingContainerQuantity
definition: The quantity of units contained in a shipping container for example 75 cases (75 CA).

name: isNutrientRelevantDataProvided
definition: Nutrient Information is populated for those values which are relevant or required to be populated on the product label or label equivalent.  All values not populated are not relevant or not required to be populated on the product label by local regulations.

name: doesTradeItemContainHumanTissue
definition: Determines whether the trade item has, as a component or ingredient, human tissue.  The amount of tissue is not limited to a certain amount, any amount will cause a flag of TRUE.

definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: registeredStatusCode
definition: The current record status of a context registered at the Global Registry for example Added, Deleted, Changed.

name: minimumHumidityPercentage
definition: The minimum humidity in percentages that the goods should be stored in.

name: codeListVersion
definition: The version of the applied size code list.

name: width
definition: The width of the trade item, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard. If the trade item is a unit load, include the shipping platform unless it is excluded according to the platformTypeCode chosen.

name: isBarCodeOnPackageVariableMeasureBarCode
definition: An indicator identifying if the bar code that is printed on the trade item package is a variable measure bar code.
