name: tradeItemGroupIdentificationCode
definition: A code assigned by the supplier or manufacturer to logically group trade item independently from the Global trade item Classification.

name: percentageOfAlcoholByVolume
definition: Percentage of alcohol contained in the base unit trade item.

name: tradeItemTechnologyDescription
definition: The type(s) of marketing name technologies contained in the appliance for example Smart Technology.

name: codeListVersion
definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

name: eUMedicalDeviceStatusCode
definition: The market status of the medical device for the EU Market. Example: On the Market, No Longer Placed on the Market.

name: packagingSustainabilityFeatureCode
definition: A feature of the packaging that contributes to sustainability initiatives for example that it is made from renewable materials.

name: priceBasisQuantity
definition: Price Basis Quantity qualifies Price with a 'Price Per' quantity. This must include a unit of measure to describe what the price and price quantity applies to, such as, a price of $100 could apply to 1 case of product or to 25 Kilos. Price Basis Quantity includes a Unit of Measure.

name: lethalConcentration50Basis
definition: The basis measurement for the measurement of Median Lethal Concentration for example 1 LT in the ratio 10 MG/1 LT .

name: codeListVersion
definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

name: fileBackgroundColourDescription
definition: A description of the colour for the background in the digital asset.  The background is the area in the asset which surrounds the item.

name: awardPrizeCode
definition: Indicates the achievement of the product in relation to a prize or award, eg winner, runner-up, shortlisted. Optional and non-repeating.

name: isImitationOrSubstitute
definition: Determines whether the trade item is an imitation or substitute product resembling the real product for example imitation eggs or milk substitute non-dairy.

name: specialItemCode
definition: This element identifies specific items for promotional, purchase eligibility and/or special tracking

name: referencedFileTypeCode
definition: The type of file that is being referenced for example Safety Data Sheet or Product Image.

name: publicationDate
definition: The date specified in the field. Mandatory in each occurrence of the composite, and non-repeating. May carry a dateformat attribute: if the attribute is missing, then indicates the format of the date; if both dateformat attribute and element are missing, the default format is YYYYMMDD.

name: warrantyDescription
definition: The description of warranty available for the trade item.

name: platformTypeCode
definition: Indicates whether the described despatch unit is delivered on a pallet/platform and on which type of platform. If the despatch unit is delivered on a platform, the platform type must be given here. The range of the platform types/codes is listed in code sets.

name: lastOrderDateTime
definition: Indicates the latest date that an order can be placed for the trade item.

name: functionalBasisUnitDescription
definition: Description of the functional basis unit.

name: isPackagingSuitableForAirShipment
definition: Determines whether or not the packaging is suitable for air shipment for passenger or cargo for example has it been air pressure tested.

name: clinicalWarningAgencyCode
definition: The agency which manages the clinical warning codings for example FDA.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: equivalentLightBulbPower
definition: Indicates the equivalent light bulb power that is defined as the power of the replaced light bulb, if the light bulb is claimed to be equivalent to the replaced light bulb type.

name: rennetTypeCode
definition: The type of rennet used for coagulation.  The enzyme rennet is used for the coagulation of the cheese mass.  Rennet and respectively similar enzymes can be gained through various processes.

name: specificGravityReferenceMaterialCode
definition: The reference material used within the ratio for specific gravity for example water or air.

name: confirmationStatusReasonCode
definition: Identifies the type issue the data recipient has with the value communicated in the attribute name.

name: packagingMaterialColourCodeReference
definition: Identifies the packaging material colour.

name: targetMarketCountryCode
definition: The code that identifies the target market. The target market is at country level or higher geographical definition and is where a trade item is intended to be sold.

name: warningsOrContraIndicationDescription
definition: Description of warnings or contra-indications applicable to the product

name: contributorRoleCode
definition: Indicates the role played by a person or corporate body in the creation of the product. Mandatory in each occurrence of the Contributor class, and may be repeated if the same person or corporate body has more than one role in relation to the product.

name: cumulativeEnergyDemandDescription
definition: The description of cumulative energy demand that is being measured for.

name: isPackagingReturnable
definition: Trade item has returnable packaging. True equals package can be returned. This attribute applies to returnable packaging with or without deposit.

name: feedLifestageCode
definition: The code, as defined by the seller, that describes the generic life stage(s) of the animal for product usage.

name: animalTargetSizeCode
definition: 1. The code, as defined by the seller, that describes the generic size of the animal, in relation to its species, for product usage.

name: animalFoodTypeCode
definition: The code that describes the shape or consistency of the animal food product.

name: packagingRecyclabilityAssessmentSpecificationCode
definition: The code that identifies the specification that defines how the degree of recyclability of packaging is calculated during assessment. These can be an agency, a regulation or directive, a community agreement, etc.

name: packagingRecyclabilityValue
definition: The value that indicates the degree of recyclability of an item's packaging, which is calculated on the basis of the standard chosen in packagingReyclabilityAssessmentSpecificationCode. This can be a percentage or value and can vary by country.

name: packagingRecyclabilityValueEffectiveDate
definition: The first date that the item with this packaging is available.

name: compositePackagingMaterialRecyclingSchemeCode
definition: The code that specifies the recycling scheme the packaging of this trade item will fall within when recycled. Applies to recyclable packaging with or without deposit.

name: packagingMaterialElementCode
definition: The code that describes the part or element of the packaging of the product associated to a material or composite material.

name: packagingMaterialRecyclingSchemeCode
definition: The code that specifies the recycling scheme the packaging of this trade item will fall within when recycled. Applies to recyclable packaging with or without deposit.

name: typeOfCleaningDisinfectionProcessCode
definition: The code that describes the type of process necessary to clean or disinfect the specific product.

name: isPreCleaningNecessary
definition: The indicator that specifies whether pre-cleaning of the product is required before cleaning and disinfection.

name: typeOfCleaningCode
definition: The code that describes the form of cleaning/detergent that can be used for the product. Example: Cleaning/detergent in accordance with ISO 15883.

name: typeOfDisinfectionCode
definition: The code that describes the type of disinfection that is possible for the product. Example: Disinfection type in accordance with ISO 15883.

name: requiredEducationTrainingTypeCode
definition: The code that describes the appropriate type of education or training required to use/handle/operate the product.

name: isProductResistantToSurfaceTensionReducingAgent
definition: The indicator that specifies whether the product is resistant to a surface tension reducing agent.

name: typeOfWasteCode
definition: The code that describes the type of waste created from the product. Please refer to any local regulation requirements for disposal/recyclable waste.

name: perfumeFragranceDilutionClassCode
definition: The code indicating the dilution class of a fragrance which indicates the concentration of fragrances within a mixture.

name: imageFacingCode
definition: The code that defines which face of the item is depicted in the image. (More information on these codes can be found in the GS1 Product Image Specification Standard for the naming conventions related to position 17 of the file name.)

name: imageStateCode
definition: The code that defines the state of the item as it is being depicted in the image. (More information on these codes can be found in  the GS1 Product Image Specification Standard for the naming conventions related to position 19 of the file name.)

name: isImageRendered
definition: The indicator that specifies if the image is the result of the creation of a digital likeness of a physical object with the use of a computer and software. Rendered images often do not begin with a photographic device.

name: imageOrientationTypeCode
definition: The code that defines the orientation/plunge (i.e., camera  angle) of the item as it is being depicted in the image. (More information on these codes can be found in the GS1 Product Image Specification Standard for the naming conventions related to position 18 of the file name.)

name: certificationStatementOnPackage
definition: The statement provided from the certification agency that must be displayed on the packaging according to the certification agreement.

name: subjectOfCertificationDescription
definition: The description that provides more information about the type of certification, e.g. the type of product, model, etc. as stated on the certificate.

name: catchCountryCode
definition: The ISO 3166-1 numeric code for the country where the fish/seafood in the product was caught or farmed.

name: fishSeafoodPresentationCode
definition: <font color="#002c6c">The code that indicates the state or form of a fish/seafood product as presented to the consumer, possibly as a result of post-catch processing (e.g., tail removed, gutted, or filleted).</font>

name: claimTypeCode
definition: The code that states the type of claim applicable to the product. It may be used alone, or in combination with Claim Element Code to identify a specific element, such as a food ingredient, chemical compound or sustainability factor, to which the claim type applies.

name: claimElementCode
definition: The code that specifies an element, such as a food ingredient, chemical compound or sustainability factor, that is subject to the claim type specified by the Claim Type Code.

name: sizeCode
definition:
A code depicting the size of an object according to a
specified list
of code

name: attributeName
definition: The name of the temporary attribute being passed as an attribute value pair.

name: attributeCode
definition: The value associated with the codeListName for example MLT for MEASUREMENT_CODE.

name: codeListNameCode
definition: The code list qualifying the temporary attribute for example MEASUREMENT_CODE.

name: codeListVersion
definition: The version of the code list qualifying the temporary attribute.

name: sustainabilityProgramCode
definition: The code identifying the sustainability program, against which the product was evaluated.

name: sustainabilityScore
definition: The score, using points or a rating system, assigned to a product by the associated sustainability program. Please refer to any local regulations concerning score.

name: sustainabilityValue
definition: The numeric value assigned to a product by the associated sustainability program. Please refer to any local regulations concerning the value.

name: rawMaterialContentPercentage
definition: The percentage of the type of raw or recycled material the product material is made from, as specified by the Raw Material Code.

name: rawMaterialCode
definition: The code describing the type of raw or recycled material the product material is made from.

name: isDesignationIntendedForSingleUse
definition: The indicator that specifies whether the product or packaging is disposable and intended to only be used once before being thrown away or recycled.

name: canMaterialsBeSeparatedManually
definition: The indicator that specifies whether the packaging materials can be separated manually without the help of tools.

name: numberOfDesignationUnits
definition: The number of designation units in the product that the material is associated to.

name: packagingClaimElementCode
definition: The code that indicates an element in the product packaging that is subject to the claim specified by the Packaging Claim Type Code.

name: isPackagingClaimMarkedOnPackage
definition: The indicator that specifies whether the claim specified by Packaging Claim Type Code in combination with Packaging Claim Element Code is stated/claimed on the product package.

name: isPackagingClaimRegulated
definition: The indicator that specifies whether the claim for the packaging is regulated for the target market.

name: packagingClaimTypeCode
definition: The code that states the type of claim relevant to the Packaging Claim Element Code.

name: messageCreatorGLN
definition: The Global Location Number (GLN) of the party responsible for creating the content contained in the message.

name: messageCreatorName
definition: The name of the party responsible for creating the content contained in the message.

name: numberOfPackagingElementUnits
definition: The number of units of the associated material element contained in the package.

name: packagingMaterialAdhesiveAmount
definition: Adhesive amount refers to the quantity or volume of adhesive material that is applied or used in a particular application or process. It represents the total quantity of adhesive substance used to bond or join two or more surfaces together.

name: packagingMaterialAdhesiveSolubilityTypeCode
definition: The code indicating how the adhesive can be dissolved or the adhesive strength of the adhesive is broken down.

name: packagingMaterialAdhesiveTypeCode
definition: The code indicating the adhesive used in the packaging or packaging material of the product.

name: extractionProcessCode
definition: The code indicating the process to remove oil or resin from plant material to make a concentrate product.

name: microbiologicalOrganismStrainCode
definition: The code indicating the strain of microbiological organism found in the product.

name: growingLightConditionTypeCode
definition: The code indicating the light conditions where plants are grown.

name: growthCycle
definition: The estimated time a seed takes from germination to vegetation.

name: tradeItemGenderTypeCode
definition: The code that indicates the gender of the animal, plant or seed that is being sold.

name: curingMethodDescription
definition: The description of the process that involves aging and drying harvested plant material, meat or fish.

name: floweringTriggerCode
definition: The code indicating the environmental factors that cause a plant to start to flower (also known as the flowering trigger point).

name: flowerTrimmingMethodCode
definition: The code indicating the method used for flower trimming and removing plant foliage during harvest.

name: carrierSubstanceTypeCode
definition: The code specifying the underlying substance (e.g., oils) that is used to absorb compounds to make them more bioavailable (i.e., easily absorbed by the body).

name: driedEquivalent
definition: The equivalent quantity amount of dried ingredient to an ingredient found in the product. The determination of this is made by the supplier and is subject to target market regulations or trade organization guidelines.

name: driedEquivalent
definition: The equivalent quantity amount of dried ingredient to an ingredient found in the product. The determination of this is made by the supplier and is subject to target market regulations or trade organization guidelines.

name: cannabinoidContentCode
definition: The code identifying how cannabinoid content (chemicals that produce psychoactive effects) is measured relative to the form of the product.

name: cannabinoidMaximumRangeValue
definition: The maximum amount of cannabinoid content (chemicals that produce psychoactive effects) per each unit of the cannabis product.

name: cannabinoidMinimumRangeValue
definition: The minimum amount of cannabinoid content (chemicals that produce psychoactive effects) per each unit of the cannabis product.

name: cannabisCBDTypeCode
definition: The code that describes the type of Cannabidiol (CBD) in a product, which is one of many active compounds found in the Cannabis plant.

name: cannabisCommonName
definition: The propriety strain name given by growers or producers of cannabis to identify their product with an existing strain or the name that was used in the legacy market.

name: cannabisPlantTypeCode
definition: The code indicating the classification of cannabis species.

name: isCannabisPlantAHybrid
definition: The indicator that specifies whether the cannabis plant is hybrid (a result of crossbreeding two other species of cannabis plants).

name: terpeneTypeCode
definition: The code indicating the type of terpene(s) (a compound that gives a product a distinctive smell or taste, especially cannabis) contained in the product.

name: maximumTerpeneContent
definition: The maximum amount of terpene(s) in the product.

name: minimumTerpeneContent
definition: The minimum amount of terpene(s) in the product.

name: medicalDeviceSoftwareCode
definition: The code that identifies if the medical device is itself software, or if the device contains software.

name: dryingMethodTypeCode
definition: Add a new attribute to identify the cannabis plant drying process.

name: cartridgeDeviceCompatibilityCode
definition: Add a new code list attribute to indicate the cartridge device compatibility

name: batteryDeviceCompatibilityStatement
definition: The statement that describes the compatibility of the battery to the type of the device.

name: vapeDeviceTypeCode
definition: The code indicating the device type for vape or electronic cigarette products, a device designed for inhaling vapor containing nicotine, cannabis or other chemicals.

name: terpeneSourceCode
definition: <sup>The code indicating the source of terpenes used in the products. </sup>

name: vapingKitCompatibilityCode
definition: The code indicating that the vaping kit is compatible with e-liquids, dry herb or both.

name: nutritionalScoreProductCategoryCode
definition: The code indicating the product category of the trade item that is used to calculate the nutritional score.

name: isPackagingElementIntendedForFoodContact
definition:
The indicator that specifies if the packaging material element is intended to come into contact with food, directly or indirectly. E.g., if any of the following is true:
• Intended to be brought into contact with food.
• Is already in contact with food.
• Can reasonably be expected to be brought into contact with food or to transfer their constituents to food under normal or foreseeable conditions of use.

name: minimumProcessTemperatureTimeSpan
definition: The minimum amount of time that the product is required to be processed, relative to the process and temperature information provided by the manufacturer, to ensure product safety or quality.

name: maximumProcessTemperatureTimeSpan
definition: The maximum amount of time that the product can safely be processed, relative to the process and temperature information provided by the manufacturer, without affecting product safety or quality.

name: packingProcessMethodCode
definition: The code indicating the process used to place the product in its packaging.

name: isSupplierARegistrant
definition: Add a new attribute to indicate specify if the supplier is a registrant or not.

name: materialDensity
definition: The density of the material expressed as its mass per unit volume, e.g., kilograms per cubic metre or pounds per cubic foot.

name: externalAgriculturalQualityStandardAgencyCode
definition: The code indicating the external agency that is responsible for the agricultural standard.

name: externalAgriculturalQualityStandardCategoryCode
definition: The code indicating the external category that describes the type of information pertaining to the agricultural code.

name: externalAgriculturalQualityStandardCode
definition: The code indicating the information related to the category for the external agricultural standard.

name: animalCutCode
definition: To support consumer facing information that helps determine proper product mix by recipient and also consumer comparaitive shopping and choices.

name: numberOfRibs
definition: The number of ribs that the trade item has.

name: multilayerFilmMaterialCompositionCode
definition: The code that defines if the multilayered film can be considered as being composed of a mono or multi material, as determined by local regulations.

name: packagingMaterialDensity
definition: The density of the packaging material expressed as its mass per unit volume, e.g., kilograms per cubic metre or pounds per cubic foot.

name: tradeItemVariantGroupCode
definition: The code that represents the variant of the trade item into a similar grouping.

name: nutrientGroupCode
definition: A code depicting a section in the nutrition or supplemented food facts table.

name: isContactInformationMarkedOnPackage
definition: The indicator that specifies whether the contact information is available on the product package.

name: isCommunicationChannelMarkedOnPackage
definition: The indicator that specifies whether the communication channel information is available on the product package.

name: fiscalYear
definition: Fiscal year is the 12-month period during which the information is applicable, relative to the end product ingredient being used in the final product. This should be tied to the applicable regulatory fiscal year for the school or other institutional meal program.

name: foodMaterialCode
definition: A code the regulator has assigned to an end product ingredient being used in the final product.

name: foodMaterialDescription
definition: Descriptive terms assigned by the regulator for the end product ingredient being used in the final product.

name: inventoryDrawdownPerTradeItem
definition: Measurement of the amount of the end product ingredient being used in the final product.

name: foodValueBasis
definition: Monetary value per unit (specified by the Food Value Basis Type Code) for the end product ingredient being used in the final product.

name: foodValueBasisTypeCode
definition: The code that indicates the basis for the monetary unit value (specified by the Food Value Basis) of the end product ingredient being used in the final product.

name: foodValuePerTradeItem
definition: Total monetary value of the end product ingredient being used in the final product. This is calculated by multiplying the Food Value Basis by the Inventory Drawdown Per Trade Item, where the UoM and the Food Value Basis Type Code align.

name: regulatorApprovalDate
definition: Date on which the regulator approved use of the specified ingredient.

name: resultingHairColourShadeCode
definition: The code that defines the hair colour shade the customer wants to achieve by using the product.

name: drinkingMaturityEndYear
definition: The year in which the drinking maturity (also known as consumption maturity) for the wine ends. It refers to the point in time at which wines develop their optimal taste.

name: drinkingMaturityStartYear
definition: The year in which the drinking maturity (also known as consumption maturity) for the wine begins. It refers to the point in time at which wines develop their optimal taste.

name: hairStyleFixationCode
definition: The code indicating the level of fixation of the hairstyle after using the product, as determined by the ability of the product to hold hair in place.

name: bristleHardnessCode
definition: The code indicating the degree of hardness of the bristles, for example for a toothbrush or an interdental brush.

name: avpList
definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

name: cfpCountryCode
definition: The code specifying a target market for which the carbon footprint values have been calculated. Transportation emissions can greatly vary from country to country.

name: cfpBoundariesCode
definition: The code identifying the life cycle stage that the product carbon footprint value refers to. The boundary setting may vary depending on the purpose of the product carbon footprint assessment.

name: cfpValue
definition: The emissions value, i.e., carbon footprint, for a specific boundary setting.

name: cfpFunctionalUnit
definition: The functional unit describes the quantity and/or performance characteristics of a product as it is used by the end-user, which forms the basis for calculating the emissions value (i.e., carbon footprint), and can be used for comparison to other similar products.

name: cfpMethodologyCode
definition: The code specifying the method used to assess and communicate the environmental impact of the product in terms of carbon footprint.

name: cfpAccountingCode
definition: The code indicating which method is used to conduct the lifecycle assessment for carbon footprint calculation.

name: edibleFatTypeCode
definition: The code indicating the fat type the trade item contains.

name: absorbencyLevel
definition: The absorbency level value, e.g., as determined within the EU based upon the number of drops of liquid the tampon can absorb.

name: numberOfPlys
definition: The number of layers or sheets within a material. The number of plys determines the thickness, strength, and stiffness of the trade item, e.g., toilet paper, tissue paper, paper towels.

name: hairColourPermanenceLevelCode
definition: The level of how long a hair colouring will last from the time applied, e.g., temporary, intensive, permanent.

name: cfpDate
definition: The date on which the product carbon footprint assessment was conducted.

name: cfpValueVerificationCode
definition: The code indicating how the calculated carbon footprint value is verified.
